name: Power Rangers
overview: A team of teenagers with attitude are recruited to save Angel Grove from the evil witch, Rita Repulsa, and later, Lord Zedd, Emperor of all he sees, and their horde of monsters.

seasons.name: Specials
seasons.overview: All the special features and Featurettes included on the Home releases of Power Rangers

seasons.name: Mighty Morphin (1)
seasons.overview: Alien sorceress Rita Repulsa and her army of monsters emerge from space to conquer Earth. All that stands in their way are five teenagers with attitude who draw on dinosaur powers to transform into the Mighty Morphin Power Rangers.

seasons.name: Mighty Morphin (2)
seasons.overview: The evil Lord Zedd arrives on the Moon, intent on conquering Earth.  To protect the world, the Power Rangers will need new Thunder Zords, new ‘teenagers with attitude,' and the help of the brand new White Ranger and his ferocious White Tiger Zord.

seasons.name: Mighty Morphin (3)
seasons.overview: Rita Repulsa's twisted family members Rito Revolto and Master Vile join forces with Lord Zedd and Rita to step up their plan to conquer Earth.  Learning the mystical arts of the ninja from the sage Ninjor, the Power Rangers battle on with magical martial arts abilities against the greatest threat of their lives.

seasons.name: Zeo
seasons.overview: The tyrannical Machine Empire arrives to conquer Earth.  Drawing on newfound powers from the legendary Zeo Crystals, the Power Rangers are reborn stronger than before.

seasons.name: Turbo
seasons.overview: The pirate queen Divatox wages war against an all new team of Power Rangers equipped with futuristic cars built for high speed battle.

seasons.name: In Space
seasons.overview: After defending the Earth against wave after wave of alien invasions, the Power Rangers finally take the fight to the stars.  With all of their villains united under the banner of the titanic villain Dark Specter, our heroes search the galaxy for their captured mentor Zordon.

seasons.name: Lost Galaxy
seasons.overview: Terra Venture – a space ship so massive it contains a city inside – embarks on an interstellar voyage to settle human pioneers on a distant planet.  A new team of Power Rangers defends the space colony from the alien armies of Trakeena in a saga that will take them to undiscovered worlds and even other galaxies.

seasons.name: Lightspeed Rescue
seasons.overview: After 5000 years of imprisonment, the demon armies of Diabolico threaten to destroy the human race, prompting a secret government agency called Lightspeed Rescue to recruit a team of heroes to protect the world as the newest Power Rangers.

seasons.name: Time Force
seasons.overview: Fugitive mutants from the distant future escape to the present to unleash a wave of crime against a helpless world but the futuristic police force known as the Power Rangers Time Force travel across time to save the past, present, and future.

seasons.name: Wild Force
seasons.overview: As the Earth's environment weakens from modern pollution, a long forgotten evil known as Master Org reawakens to destroy Mother Nature.  The mythical Wild Zords – mammoth animals of yesteryear thought to be extinct – choose a team of brave youths to defend the Earth as the Power Rangers Wild Force.

seasons.name: Ninja Storm
seasons.overview: A group of teenagers trained in the arts of the stealthy ninja warrior unite to protect the world from an exiled evil ninja master determined to conquer the world.

seasons.name: Dino Thunder
seasons.overview: When the wicked Mesogog attempts to revert the Earth back to a prehistoric age of dinosaurs, legendary veteran Ranger Tommy Oliver returns to action.  Recruiting a soccer prodigy, a computer expert, and a fledgling musician to harness their own powers derived from dinosaurs, they must unite as the Power Rangers Dino Thunder to protect the Earth.

seasons.name: S.P.D.
seasons.overview: In the near future, an elite police force of Power Rangers dedicated to justice fight to save the Earth from an alien invasion led by Emperor Gruumm.

seasons.name: Mystic Force
seasons.overview: Legend says when the Darkness arises, five brave teen Sorcerers will be called to fight for the planet's survival. With guidance from their wise mentor and the ancient Xenotome, Book of the Unknown, they will embark on magical adventures, befriend mystical dragons, battle dangerous beasts, encounter pure evil, and transform into the Power Rangers Mystic Force.

seasons.name: Operation Overdrive
seasons.overview: When an archaeologist finds a legendary artifact known as the Corona Aurora, or ‘Crown of the Gods,' two ancient evil brothers, Flurious and Moltor, travel to Earth, stopping at nothing to obtain its limitless power.  It's up to the Power Rangers – an elite team of treasure-hunters – to travel the globe to find the ancient jewels that power the crown before Flurious and Moltor's minions can find them first.

seasons.name: Jungle Fury
seasons.overview: When the ancient evil spirit Dai Shi returns to wipe out all humans, a trio of teenagers must learn secret kung fu styles based on the world's most ferocious jungle animals to become Power Rangers and save the world.

seasons.name: R.P.M.
seasons.overview: In a bleak near future, the Venjix Computer Network and its robot armies have almost completely conquered the world.  In the dome-shielded city of Corinth, a group of heroes equipped with high tech Racing Performance Machines fight a desperate battle for survival as the Power Rangers RPM.

seasons.name: Samurai
seasons.overview: A new generation of Power Rangers must master the ancient Symbols of Samurai Power which give them control over the elements of Fire, Water, Sky, Forest, and Earth.  Under the guidance of their all-knowing mentor and the aid of their devoted animal Zords, they battle the dark forces of the Netherworld and a mysterious Warrior bent on destruction.

seasons.name: Super Samurai
seasons.overview: The Samurai Power Rangers continue their battle against the evil Master Xandred who has now joined forces with the malevolent Serrator.  To fight this growing threat, the Samurai Rangers learn to use the legendary Black Box to form all new Megazord combinations and become Super Samurai.   Through teamwork, they also learn to invoke the power of their ancestors to morph into Shogun Mode and protect humanity from the Netherworld's vile villains.

seasons.name: Megaforce
seasons.overview: For centuries, the earth has been protected by a supernatural guardian named Gosei and his robotic aide, Tensou.  When the evil Warstar aliens plan a massive invasion of Earth, Gosei calls upon five teenagers with talent and attitude to form the ultimate team…the Power Rangers Megaforce!  Using their newfound special abilities, mega-weapons, high-tech Zords and giant Megazords to battle this new alien threat, the Power Rangers Megaforce prove that “Earth's defenders never surrender!”  Go Go Megaforce!

seasons.name: Super Megaforce
seasons.overview: Ruthless Prince Vekar has arrived with his massive alien Armada to conquer the earth.  To face this new threat, Gosei gives the MEGAFORCE RANGERS special Morphers and Keys, which allow them to morph into SUPER MEGAFORCE RANGERS!  Using these special Keys, they also have the amazing new ability to morph into any team of Legendary Rangers from the past.  Super-sized villains, super-sized powers and action-packed adventure can only mean one thing: the all-new POWER RANGERS SUPER MEGAFORCE has arrived!

seasons.name: Dino Charge
seasons.overview: Millions of years ago, an intergalactic bounty hunter named Sledge tried desperately to capture the 10 mysterious Energems, each capable of filling whomever possessed them with incredible powers. Keeper, the wise and ancient guardian of the Energems, entrusted each Energem to the Earth's mightiest beasts, the dinosaurs, for protection. Centuries later after the dinosaurs went extinct, some of the Energems were discovered by humans. Those who proved worthy gained the ability to morph into Power Rangers. But now, Sledge has returned and has vowed to capture the Energems at all costs. It is up to the Power Rangers Dino Charge to hunt down the rest of the Energems and defeat Sledge once and for all!

seasons.name: Dino Super Charge
seasons.overview: The Power Rangers continue their search for the Energems after Sledge’s defeat, but soon learn that his most dangerous prisoner, the evil Heckyl, survived! In light of this new threat, Kendall creates a powerful new Dino Charger that unlocks the Red Ranger’s T-Rex Super Charge mode! It will take every Zord, Megazord, and Dino Charger in the Power Rangers’ arsenal to finally unite all ten Energems and save the universe!

seasons.name: Ninja Steel
seasons.overview: Deep in space, Galvanax is the reigning champion of the most popular game show in the universe, “Galaxy Warriors”. Galvanax sends his warrior contestants to Earth to steal the Ninja Power Stars, where each battle against the Power Rangers is broadcast throughout the universe. The Power Rangers must master their arsenal of Ninja Power Stars, Zords and Megazords to stop this evil threat and save Earth from destruction.

seasons.name: Super Ninja Steel
seasons.overview: With Galvanax’s defeat and Brody and Aiden’s reunion with their father, all finally seems to be safe in Summer Cove. But when the Rangers are alerted to Madame Odius’ presence on Earth, they discover that she has obtained the powerful Ninja Super Steel and is still after the Ninja Nexus Prism! Luckily the Rangers are able to use the powerful new steel to create brand new Ninja Power Stars. It’s going to take everything in the arsenal, including brand new Megazords, to protect the Ninja Nexus Prism and defeat Odius once and for all!

seasons.name: Beast Morphers (1)
seasons.overview: Set in the future, a secret agency combines a newly discovered substance called “Morph-X” with animal DNA to create the Power Rangers Beast Morphers team. The Rangers must fight off an evil sentient computer virus bent on taking over the source of all Ranger power, the Morphin Grid itself

seasons.name: Beast Morphers (2)
seasons.overview: As Evox builds his army to overtake Earth, the Rangers must stop him with new zords, enhanced abilities and unexpected allies.

seasons.name: Dino Fury (1)
seasons.overview: When an army of powerful alien beings is unleashed on Earth threatening life as we know it, a brand-new team of Power Rangers, fueled by the pre-historic power of the dinosaurs, are recruited to deal with the threat.

seasons.name: Dino Fury (2)
seasons.overview: The Power Rangers band together with mighty new Dino Keys to stop more squads of Sporix beasts — and revived enemies out for revenge.

seasons.name: Cosmic Fury
seasons.overview: When Lord Zedd returns more powerful than ever, Team Cosmic Fury takes to the cosmos to battle the emperor of evil — and save the universe as we know it.

episodes.overview: The Rangers locate the Temple of Power, and within find its occupant, Ninjor, passing a test of dismissal. With his help, the Rangers soon undergo a ritual that provides them with new powers. Meanwhile, outside the temple, the Tenga forces continue to gather.

episodes.name: Ninja Quest (4)
episodes.overview: Returning to Angel Grove with their powers restored and with new Zords at their command, the Rangers gain a measure of revenge on a giant sized Rito. Meanwhile the evil Vampirus egg hatches outside of the Temple, and the creature soon initiates a confrontation with Ninjor.

episodes.name: A Brush with Destiny
episodes.overview: Based on Kimberly's dream, Rita and Zedd create the Artistmole monster who steals the color out of life.

episodes.name: Passing the Lantern
episodes.overview: Rita and Zedd attempt to steal Adam's heirloom lantern for its power.

episodes.name: Wizard for a Day
episodes.overview: Rito and Zedd turn a science teacher into "Marvo the Meanie" as Rocky attempts to teach his class.

episodes.name: Fourth Down and Long
episodes.overview: Rocky must drop kick Rita and Zedd to save the Rangers from Centiback, a monster who changes people into footballs.

episodes.name: Stop the Hate Master (1)
episodes.overview: The Hate Master causes the Power Rangers to fight among themselves and make plans to quit.

episodes.name: Stop the Hate Master (2)
episodes.overview: Aisha holds the secret to stopping the Hate Master and reuniting the Rangers.

episodes.name: Final Face-Off
episodes.overview: When Rita awakens The Face Stealer, the Rangers must stop him from stealing the faces of Angel Grove citizens. He proves to be quite the challenge when he manages to steal a few Ranger faces as well.

episodes.name: The Potion Notion
episodes.overview: Rito's love potion creates havoc in Angel Grove.

episodes.name: A Ranger Catastrophe (1)
episodes.overview: Rita corrupts and brainwashes a girl named Kat, whose family has just moved to Angel Grove, to serve her. She steals Kimberly's Power Coin, causing the Pink Ranger to be drained of her energy.

episodes.name: A Ranger Catastrophe (2)
episodes.overview: Katherine steals Kimberly's Power Coin, causing the Pink Ranger to be drained of her energy.

episodes.name: Changing of the Zords (1)
episodes.overview: Zedd and Rita capture Ninjor and his power source with plans to activate a set of dormant Zords.

episodes.name: Changing of the Zords (2)
episodes.overview: Zedd uses the kidnapped Kimberly to blackmail the Rangers.

episodes.name: Changing of the Zords (3)
episodes.overview: Kimberly's safety depends on the Rangers piloting Zedd's Zords.

episodes.name: Follow that Cab!
episodes.overview: Kimberly, Bulk, and Skull are taken on a wild ride by the Crabbie Cabbie monster.

episodes.name: A Different Shade of Pink (1)
episodes.overview: Rita vows to keep Kimberly out of the gymnastics competition for the Pan Global Games.

episodes.name: A Different Shade of Pink (2)
episodes.overview: Rita and Zedd use Ninjor to bargain for the return of Katherine.

episodes.name: A Different Shade of Pink (3)
episodes.overview: Kimberly has to make the most critical decision of her life, to stay a Power Ranger, or follow her dream to become a world class gymnast.

episodes.name: Rita's Pita
episodes.overview: The junk food Ravenator threatens to destroy Tommy -- from the inside out.

episodes.name: Another Brick in the Wall
episodes.overview: Katherine and Billy try to save the other Rangers from the Brick Bully.

episodes.name: A Chimp in Charge
episodes.overview: Rita and Zedd change a pet chimp used by Katherine and Aisha for a school project into a Sinister Simian.

episodes.name: Master Vile and the Metallic Armor (1)
episodes.overview: Rita's father, Master Vile, arrives to do what she and Zedd have failed to do -- destroy the Rangers.

episodes.name: Master Vile and the Metallic Armor (2)
episodes.overview: Master Vile and his evil crew appear to be winning the battle against the Power Rangers.

episodes.name: Master Vile and the Metallic Armor (3)
episodes.overview: The Rangers decide the only way to win against Master Vile is to journey to a distant galaxy.

episodes.name: I'm Dreaming of a White Ranger
episodes.overview: The Power Rangers are forced to try to save Christmas -- without their powers.

episodes.name: The Sound of Dischordia
episodes.overview: Master Vile has sent the devious Dischordia to put the Power Rangers under a terrible tune.

episodes.name: Rangers in Reverse
episodes.overview: Master Vile turns back time to gain control of the Earth and turn the Rangers into helpless children.

episodes.name: Alien Rangers of Aquitar (1)
episodes.overview: Zordon calls on the Alien Rangers to help defend the Earth after the Power Rangers are made helpless.

episodes.name: Alien Rangers of Aquitar (2)
episodes.overview: Alien Rangers defends the Earth against Master Vile and his army of monsters.

episodes.name: Climb Every Fountain
episodes.overview: Billy and the young Rangers devise a scheme to outsmart the monsters.

episodes.name: The Alien Trap
episodes.overview: Billy and the young Rangers attempt to free the Alien Rangers from a toxic lake.

episodes.name: Attack of the 60' Bulk
episodes.overview: Rita and Zedd turn Bulk into the Brat Boy monster.

episodes.name: Water You Thinking?
episodes.overview: With the child Rangers journeying through a time portal, Zedd sends Witchblade to keep the Alien Rangers from hydrating.

episodes.name: Along Came a Spider
episodes.overview: In the distant past, Adam searches across Korea for his Zeo Crystal.

episodes.name: Sowing the Seas of Evil
episodes.overview: As Katherine and Tommy seek their crystals, Lord Zedd, aiming to thwart the Alien Rangers, prepares to bring the Emperor of the Dark Waters of Aquitar, Hydro Hog, to Earth.

episodes.name: Hogday Afternoon (1)
episodes.overview: Zedd and Rita send the Hydro Hog to Earth to suck up all the water.

episodes.name: Hogday Afternoon (2)
episodes.overview: Aisha faces a difficult decision in her Zeo Quest while the Alien Rangers battle Hydro Hog.

3.name: Mighty Morphin (3)
3.overview: Rita Repulsa's twisted family members Rito Revolto and Master Vile join forces with Lord Zedd and Rita to step up their plan to conquer Earth.  Learning the mystical arts of the ninja from the sage Ninjor, the Power Rangers battle on with magical martial arts abilities against the greatest threat of their lives.

episodes.name: A Zeo Beginning (1)
episodes.overview: In the rubble of the destroyed Command Center, the Power Rangers find the Zeo Crystal.

episodes.name: A Zeo Beginning (2)
episodes.overview: The Rangers face their greatest challenge as Zordon explains that King Mondo is preparing to invade the Solar System, his final link in a chain of galaxies he already controls.

episodes.name: The Shooting Star
episodes.overview: When Mondo and Machina unleash the Staroid on the Zeo Rangers, they are forced to call on their untested Zeo Zords.

episodes.name: Target Rangers
episodes.overview: The computer software that Rocky, and his new friend Jennifer are working on, is stolen by the Cogs and used against the Rangers.

episodes.name: For Cryin' Out Loud
episodes.overview: Tommy and Katherine take care of a baby for a school assignment giving King Mondo an idea for his evil ambitions.

episodes.name: Rangers in the Outfield
episodes.overview: The teens' baseball team provides the perfect outlet for Prince Sprocket to do battle with the Rangers when he turns their batting machine into the People Pitcher.

episodes.name: Every Dog Has His Day
episodes.overview: Smokey, a specially trained dog, aids the Zeo Rangers in fighting Digster, Mondo and Machina's latest monster.

episodes.name: The Puppet Blaster
episodes.overview: When Ernie brings a puppet show to the Youth Center to entertain the children of Angel Grove, Mondo and Machina hatch a plan to control the children's minds, by planting a transmitter on the Puppet Man.

episodes.name: Invasion of the Ranger Snatchers
episodes.overview: Prince Sprocket recruits the Rangers to be in his own twisted movie; "Invasion of the Ranger Snatchers."

episodes.name: Graduation Blues
episodes.overview: As Billy learns he has accumulated enough credits to graduate from Angel Grove High, Cestro, the Blue Alien Ranger, lands on Earth seeking Billy's help.

episodes.name: A Few Bad Seeds
episodes.overview: As Rocky and Adam work on developing hybrid plants for Botany class, Rocky's plant exhibits weird behavior, growing rapidly and developing an appetite for metal.

episodes.name: Instrument of Destruction
episodes.overview: A mysterious musician in Angel Grove High is pursued by Prince Sprocket and King Mondo.

episodes.name: Mean Screen
episodes.overview: Tanya and Adam are exploring the new world of cyberspace with the help of Raymond, a computer whiz, at school. When they run into a computer virus, Mondo gets the idea to create Mean Screen, a horrible computer monster that will infect all of the computers in Angel Grove.

episodes.name: Mr. Billy's Wild Ride
episodes.overview: As Billy is returning from Aquitar in a space capsule, Machina and Mondo attack his space craft, sending it into the gravitational pull of the Machine Skybase.

episodes.name: There's No Business Like Snow Business (1)
episodes.overview: Tommy receives a "Dear John" letter.

episodes.name: There's No Business Like Snow Business (2)
episodes.overview: Mondo and Machina send the Defoliator to create a greenhouse effect in Angel Grove.

episodes.name: There's No Business Like Snow Business (3)
episodes.overview: As Katherine tries to console Tommy about his "Dear John" letter from Kimberly, a spark of attraction begins to form between the two Rangers.

episodes.name: Inner Spirit
episodes.overview: On a journey to find True of Heart, Tommy comes upon the incredible discovery of a young man who looks just like him.

episodes.name: Challenges
episodes.overview: Searching for the other half of an arrowhead, Tommy discovers its owner is his brother.

episodes.name: Found and Lost
episodes.overview: Having kidnapped Tommy's newfound brother David, King Mondo blackmails Tommy into giving up his half of the arrowhead, in order to set David free.

episodes.name: Brother, Can You Spare an Arrowhead?
episodes.overview: Now that he has both halves of the arrowhead, King Mondo vows to destroy the Zeo Rangers, while continuing to refuse the release of Tommy's brother.

episodes.name: Trust in Me
episodes.overview: King Mondo sends down the Defector robot to trick the Zeo Rangers into gaining their trust, and thereby able to destroy them.

episodes.name: It Came from Angel Grove
episodes.overview: Adam experiences a nightmarish scenario when the Machine Empire invades Earth overnight and transforms many of Adam's friends into sinister scientists, werewolves, and dark forces.

episodes.name: Bulk Fiction
episodes.overview: Bulk's infatuation with the daughter of a high ranking officer soon puts both his, Skull's, and Lt. Stone's careers in jeopardy.

episodes.name: Song Sung Yellow
episodes.overview: Tanya's potential new singing career divides her time between fulfilling an ambition and serving as a Ranger

episodes.name: Game of Honor
episodes.overview: King Mondo attempts to rule the Earth's waterways by building a fleet of ships under an invisible field.

episodes.name: The Power of Gold
episodes.overview: King Mondo's plan to divide and conquer the Zeo Rangers is spoiled by the appearance of the Gold Ranger.

episodes.name: A Small Problem
episodes.overview: The other Rangers must find a way to help their friends when Prince Sprocket shrinks Tommy and Katherine and places them in a terrarium with a hungry spider.

episodes.name: Oily to Bed, Oily to Rise
episodes.overview: Katherine competes in a surfing competition, but faces danger when the Leaky Faucet monster puts toxic Cog oil in all the water in Angel Grove.

episodes.name: Rock-a-Bye Power Rangers
episodes.overview: The Somnibot casts a sleeping spell on the people of Angel Grove, leaving it to the Gold Ranger to break the spell.

episodes.name: Do I Know You?
episodes.overview: The Gold Ranger finds asylum in the Power Chamber from the evil Mondo, Machina, and the Varox bounty hunter.

episodes.name: Revelations of Gold
episodes.overview: When the Gold Ranger is attacked by Varox Bounty Hunters, Pyramidas is hit, and falls into the seas of the planet Aquitar.

episodes.name: A Golden Homecoming
episodes.overview: Time is running out for transference of the Golden Powers.

episodes.name: Mondo's Last Stand
episodes.overview: King Mondo is determined to use the Damocles Sword to destroy the Zeo Rangers.

episodes.name: Bomber in the Summer
episodes.overview: The teens are helping Ernie set up for his new Beach Club when a group of tough teens ride in and begin to trash the place.

episodes.name: Scent of a Weasel
episodes.overview: The teens are involved in a charity fashion show for the famous designer, Mr. Stenchy.

episodes.name: The Lore of Auric
episodes.overview: Aisha sends Tanya a map of Mysterio Island, the island on which Tanya suspects her parents have been missing for years.

episodes.name: The Ranger Who Came in from the Gold
episodes.overview: When Katherine stages a ballet about King Midas, Louie Kaboom creates the Midas Hound, an idol that changes everything into gold.

episodes.name: The Joke's on Blue
episodes.overview: A practical joker wrecks havoc on Angel Grove High. While Bulk and Skull try to track down the trickster, Prince Sprocket's brother, Prince Gasket and sister-in-law, Archerina, arrive with a few new tricks of their own!

episodes.name: Where In The World is Zeo Ranger 5?
episodes.overview: While jet skiing on the lake, Tommy is mysteriously disappears.

episodes.name: King for a Day (1)
episodes.overview: The Zeo Rangers discover that Tommy has been captured by Prince Gasket, and placed in a large arena with monsters battling one another.

episodes.name: King for a Day (2)
episodes.overview: The Gold Ranger is forced to defend himself when the brainwashed Tommy attacks him.

episodes.name: A Brief Mystery of Time
episodes.overview: Tommy is confused when he keeps reliving experiences of the day over and over.

episodes.name: A Mystery to Me
episodes.overview: The teens all dress in classic mystery character costumes when they participate in a charity dinner organized by Detective Stone.

episodes.name: Another Song and Dance
episodes.overview: Tommy asks Tanya for voice lessons when he has to sing in front of the class.

episodes.name: Rangers of Two Worlds (1)
episodes.overview: Everyone is stunned when it is revealed that Billy has aged into an old man.

episodes.name: Rangers of Two Worlds (2)
episodes.overview: The Power Rangers Zeo team up with the Alien Rangers of Aquitar to combat a double threat from King Mondo and Lord Zedd.

episodes.name: Hawaii Zeo
episodes.overview: The golden powers start to fade from Jason.

episodes.name: Good as Gold
episodes.overview: Jason, who is continuing to lose the golden powers, is confronted by Rita and Lord Zedd.

episodes.name: A Season to Remember
episodes.overview: The Rangers, together with their friend Raymond, help Ernie set up for a multicultural holiday banquet, and in the process learn how different cultures celebrate the holidays.

4.name: Zeo
4.overview: The tyrannical Machine Empire arrives to conquer Earth.  Drawing on newfound powers from the legendary Zeo Crystals, the Power Rangers are reborn stronger than before.

episodes.name: Shift into Turbo (1)
episodes.overview: Divatox returns to Earth seeking vengeance against the Power Rangers.

episodes.name: Shift into Turbo (2)
episodes.overview: With Justin busy fighting Elgar, Divatox attacks Tanya, Adam, and Katherine. Meanwhile, Zordon and Alpha are keeping a secret from the Rangers.

episodes.name: Shift into Turbo (3)
episodes.overview: The results of Justin's test are in, and as it turns out, he's going to be starting high school due to being a genius. Zordon reveals that he and Alpha are returning to Eltar with Lerigot. Divatox begins trying to close the wormhole that is taking Zordon and Alpha home.

episodes.name: Shadow Rangers
episodes.overview: Divatox sends the evil Chromite monster to Angel Grove with a detonator. When the Rangers try to stop him, he steals their morphing powers to create the Shadow Rangers. Tommy is forced to find a way to stop Chromite and track down his missing friends by himself.

episodes.name: Transmission Impossible
episodes.overview: Visceron travels from the planet Inquiris to deliver some startling news to Dimitria. Divatox learns of this and captures him. She then turns him against the Rangers when he refuses to tell her his message.

episodes.name: Rally Ranger
episodes.overview: Trying to impress his aunt Divatox, Elgar decides to sabotage Justin's box car race with a detonator he made himself. Meanwhile, Porto goes AWOL and attacks the city.

episodes.name: Built for Speed
episodes.overview: Some of Adam's friends decide to settle an argument by drag racing. Divatox's Demon Racer plants a detonator in one of their cars. The Rangers have to defeat the Demon Racer and stop the detonator before it blows.

episodes.name: Bicycle Built For The Blues
episodes.overview: It's Justin's birthday and Divatox has sent him a gift. The Rangers have to get Justin off his new bike before it explodes in 25 miles. If that was not bad enough, Divatox sends Big Burpa to distract them.

episodes.name: The Whole Lie
episodes.overview: During a volunteer car wash, Porto appears and plants a detonator. Justin spots him and the Mouthpiece monster attacks him and makes it so he can only tell lies. Meanwhile, Porto has made it so anytime one of the Rangers lie, a Pirahantron attacks.

episodes.name: Glyph Hanger
episodes.overview: Divatox summons her ancient Egyptian ex-fiance Pharaoh to battle the Turbo Rangers.

episodes.name: Weight and See
episodes.overview: Due to an insult from a rival ballet dancer, Kat is worried over her weight. Divatox sends Numbor to attack the Rangers, rendering Kat weightless.

episodes.name: Alarmed and Dangerous
episodes.overview: Divatox plants a detonator on a firetruck and has her Pirahantrons set off fire alarms all over the city. Meanwhile, Justin has his own problems with some bullies from school, and he almost gets caught teleporting.

episodes.name: The Millenium Message
episodes.overview: The Blue Senturion, an intergalactic law enforcement robot, arrives from the year 2000 with a message for Dimitria; Lord Zedd, Rita, The Machine Empire and Divatox will team up to destroy the universe. When Divatox learns of this message, she reprograms the Blue Senturion to think the Rangers are evil.

episodes.name: A Drive To Win
episodes.overview:
Divatox plants a detonator in the scoreboard at one of Adam's soccer games. If Angel Grove scores 4 points, it will go off. She sends Electrovolt to distract the Rangers.

First appearance of Ashley and Carlos.

episodes.name: Cars Attacks
episodes.overview: Lt. Stone's niece, Jenny, competes with Kat to get into London's Royal Dance Academy. Divatox decides to plant a detonator at the competition, disguised as a cassette player, and sends Wolfgang Amadeus Griller to distract the Rangers.

episodes.name: Honey, I Shrunk The Rangers (1)
episodes.overview: Divatox sends Shrinkasect to mess with the Blue Senturion's hardware. The Shrinkasect monster shrinks the Rangers while Justin is trying to stop Bulk and Skulls car.

episodes.name: Honey, I Shrunk The Rangers (2)
episodes.overview: The Rangers attempt to break out of Divatox's submarine. Meanwhile, Justin tries to unshrink the Blue Senturion and find the detonator that Bulk and Skull have mistakenly taken.

episodes.name: Passing the Torch (1)
episodes.overview: The Rangers prepare for their final assignment while Divatox decides to capture Tommy.

episodes.name: Passing the Torch (2)
episodes.overview: Tommy, Kat, Adam, and Tanya pass their powers on to a new generation of Power Rangers.

episodes.name: Stitch Witchery
episodes.overview: Divatox uses Ashley's fashion jacket to control the minds of the citizens of Angel Grove as well as the Blue Senturion.

episodes.name: The Wheel of Fate
episodes.overview: Two intelligent cars from outer space called Lightning Cruiser and Storm Blaster travel to Earth.

episodes.name: Trouble by the Slice
episodes.overview: Divatox is struck by amnesia while the Power Rangers battle evil pizzas.

episodes.name: The Phantom Phenomenon
episodes.overview: The mysterious Phantom Ranger appears on Earth to assist the Power Rangers.

episodes.name: Vanishing Act
episodes.overview: The Rangers try to uncover why everything around them is disappearing including the Power Chamber.

episodes.name: When Time Freezes Over
episodes.overview: Divatox attempts to control time in order to freeze the planet Earth.

episodes.name: The Darkest Day
episodes.overview: General Havoc reinforces Divatox helping her capture the Turbo Megazord.

episodes.name: One Last Hope
episodes.overview: With no way to defend Angel Grove, the Rangers turn to the Phantom Ranger for assistance.

episodes.name: The Fall of the Phantom
episodes.overview: General Havoc and Divatox set a trap for the Phantom Ranger in order to capture his powerful Phantom Ruby.

episodes.name: Clash of the Megazords
episodes.overview: The Turbo Rangers race to stop the Turbo Megazord and save the Phantom Ranger as his life force ebbs away.

episodes.name: The Robot Ranger
episodes.overview: Justin suspects that his fellow Rangers have been replaced by robots.

episodes.name: Beware the Third Wish
episodes.overview: The Wicked Wisher grants Divatox three wishes. One of which she uses to turn the Blue Senturion evil.

episodes.name: The Gardener of Evil
episodes.overview: The Power Rangers hurry to find the third wishing coin and restore the Blue Senturion.

episodes.name: Fire In Your Tank
episodes.overview: The Torch Tiger steals the Turbo Rangers' super fuel turning him into an arsonist nightmare.

episodes.name: The Turn of the Wretched Wrench
episodes.overview: Ashley finds her auto mechanics class more difficult than she anticipated which is further complicated by her fellow student, the Maniac Mechanic.

episodes.name: Spirit of the Woods
episodes.overview: T.J. meets a mysterious young boy in the forest named Erutan.

episodes.name: The Song of Confusion
episodes.overview: Cassie's new rock band turns out to be more than she bargained for.

episodes.name: The Accident
episodes.overview: When Carlos injures a rival, even he isn't sure if it was really by accident.

episodes.name: Cassie’s Best Friend
episodes.overview: As Elgar repairs his Zord, Cassie loses her dog Jetson, but meets a mysterious new friend who knows her better than anyone.

episodes.name: The Curve Ball
episodes.overview: T.J. needs to learn how to hit a curve ball if he's going to save his baseball team's chances of victory as well as the world.

episodes.name: Carlos and the Count
episodes.overview: An encounter with a mutated lunar bat leaves Carlos with an aversion to sunlight, and a powerful thirst - for blood!

episodes.name: Little Strong Man
episodes.overview: Justin is given superhuman strength when a radioactive ant bites him. Meanwhile, Divatox pilots the first of her Divazords into battle against the Rangers.

episodes.name: The Rival Rangers
episodes.overview: Cassie and Ashley compete for the new kid in school's affections while Porto pilots the Shark Zord into battle.

episodes.name: Parts and Parcel
episodes.overview: T.J. tries to help Bulk and Skull find out who is raiding Angel Grove for spare parts.

episodes.name: Chase Into Space (1)
episodes.overview: Justin faces the possibility of having to move away as against overwhelming odds, the Turbo Rangers charge into their final battle.

episodes.name: Chase Into Space (2)
episodes.overview: The remaining Power Rangers blast off into outer space to try and save Zordon.

5.name: Turbo
5.overview: The pirate queen Divatox wages war against an all new team of Power Rangers equipped with futuristic cars built for high speed battle.

episodes.name: From Out of Nowhere (1)
episodes.overview: The Rangers and Alpha 6 are sucked into an unknown high tech space ship. Meanwhile, Dark Specter assembles many of the universe's most evil villains.

episodes.name: From Out of Nowhere (2)
episodes.overview: With the Astro Megaship stranded on an uninhabited planet and Astronema's forces closing in, the Red Ranger reveals his identity to the Rangers and presents them with new powers.

episodes.name: Save Our Ship
episodes.overview: The Power Rangers return home to an explosive welcome on Earth from Ecliptor and Astronema.

episodes.name: Shell Shocked
episodes.overview: The Space Rangers meet the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles.

episodes.name: Never Stop Searching
episodes.overview: Andros investigates some energy readings coming from KO-35, believing it to be his lost sister. What he finds is Ecliptor waiting for him instead.

episodes.name: Satellite Search
episodes.overview: A satellite holding valuable information crash lands on the planet Kalderon. The Rangers find it, but Astronema battles the Rangers and steals it from them. She ties the Rangers up to be eaten by a Clawhammer.

episodes.name: A Ranger Among Thieves
episodes.overview: Andros befriends a trio of thieves, who become endangered when a monster who can harness electricity attacks their stolen car hideout.

episodes.name: When Push Comes to Shove
episodes.overview: Cassie is blackmailed into going out with a loser, who she finds out to not be such a bad guy. The date goes awry when one of Astronema's monsters tries to knock down the building they are in, which happens to contain a nuclear device.

episodes.name: The Craterite Invasion
episodes.overview: A Simudeck malfunction causes the Craterites to multiply, escape, and attack Angel Grove.

episodes.name: The Wasp With A Heart
episodes.overview: A wasp monster doesn't have it in him to be evil, and he helps and befriends Cassie, who sticks up for him when confronted by the other Rangers. But the Rangers have to deal with the evil Sting King.

episodes.name: The Delta Discovery
episodes.overview: The Phantom Ranger discovers where Dark Specter is hiding Zordon.

episodes.name: The Great Evilyzer
episodes.overview: Professor Phenomenus develops a ray that can turn objects evil. Astronema decides to use it against the Rangers by turning the Delta Megazord evil.

episodes.name: Grandma Matchmaker
episodes.overview: Ashley's grandmother visits Angel Grove intent on seeing Ashley engaged before she leaves, and she inadvertently gets caught up in one of the Rangers' battles.

episodes.name: The Barillian Sting
episodes.overview: A sting from an alien insect causes Carlos to mutate. Carlos then stings Cassie, who also mutates. The Rangers manage to defeat the alien insect, turned into one of Astronema's monsters, and cure Cassie and Carlos before they destroy the ship.

episodes.name: T.J.’s Identity Crisis
episodes.overview: A blow to the head causes TJ to lose his memory, just as three Rangers are captured by Darkonda, who has absorbed Ecliptor and become Darkliptor.

episodes.name: Flashes of Darkonda
episodes.overview: Andros does some undercover work on an alien planet, where Darkonda is hanging out at a casino. Andros manages to beat a group of aliens in a game of cards, and win Zordon's key cards. Andros escapes the planet, and finally remembers that it was Darkonda who had kidnapped his long lost sister.

episodes.name: The Rangers' Mega Voyage
episodes.overview: The Rangers find the location of the Mega Vehicles - five powerful space crafts which combine to form the Mega Voyager, and gain control of them with Zordon's key cards.

episodes.name: True Blue to the Rescue
episodes.overview: The Rangers are captured by Astronema while trying to save Storm Blaster. Storm Blaster escapes and brings back Blue Turbo Ranger Justin, who saves the Rangers, is reunited with his former teammates and is also introduced to Andros as they go to rescue Lightning Cruiser.

episodes.name: Invasion of the Body Switcher
episodes.overview: A monster with the ability to alter appearances changes Astronema into Ashley, allowing her to sneak aboard the Megaship. She captures all of the rangers except Andros. Ashley tricks the monster and Elgar after she transforms into Astronema, which allows her to escape and work to save the other rangers.

episodes.name: Survival of the Silver
episodes.overview: While on a hostile alien world, the Megaship is attacked, damaging the cryogenic chamber which holds Zhane, the Silver Ranger. As the Rangers defend the Megaship, Zhane steps out and lends a hand, much to the surprise of Andros, who had placed him in cryo-stasis due to serious injuries.

episodes.name: Red with Envy
episodes.overview: Andros is infuriated when he suspects that Zhane is trying to put the moves on Ashley. This leads to him order that Zhane stay on the ship while the Rangers go down and battle, but it turns out that they really need him, as Zhane goes down also and helps them out.

episodes.name: The Silver Secret
episodes.overview: A diagnostic reveals that Zhane only has a limited time to stay morphed. Astronema deduces this, and sends down a monster to exploit this weakness.

episodes.name: A Date with Danger
episodes.overview: When Astronema is attacked by one of her own monsters, Zhane comes to her rescue, and the two find that they are strongly attracted to each other.

episodes.name: Zhane’s Destiny
episodes.overview: The Rangers investigate readings from a planet, and find that the rebels from KO-35 have set up camp there. Darkonda is among them, in disguise as an officer, who tries to turn the people against the Rangers.

episodes.name: Always a Chance
episodes.overview: After accidentally hurting Cassie in battle, Carlos finds his self-confidence shaken prompting an old Mighty Morphin friend to lend a hand.

episodes.name: The Secret of the Locket
episodes.overview: When Darkonda sets a trap for the Red Ranger, Andros finally comes face to face with his long-lost sister.

episodes.name: Astronema Thinks Twice
episodes.overview: Astronema questions her own motives as she travels to KO-35 to battle the Power Rangers.

episodes.name: The Rangers’ Leap of Faith
episodes.overview: The Power Rangers question whether they can trust Astronema when she offers to help them find Zordon.

episodes.name: Dark Specter’s Revenge (1)
episodes.overview: With a new ally aboard the Megaship, the Rangers race to save the Earth from an asteroid on a collision course with the planet.

episodes.name: Dark Specter’s Revenge (2)
episodes.overview: An old ally returns to help Andros rescue his sister from Dark Specter

episodes.name: Rangers Gone Psycho
episodes.overview: Astronema assembles a team of evil Psycho Rangers to solidify her power.

episodes.name: Carlos On Call
episodes.overview: Carlos must appease a little girl's every whim to keep his identity a secret.

episodes.name: A Rift in the Rangers
episodes.overview: The Psycho Rangers take advantage of the animosity between the Ranger girls to capture Ashley.

episodes.name: Five of a Kind
episodes.overview: T.J. devises a clever strategy to defeat the Psycho Rangers in battle.

episodes.name: Silence is Golden
episodes.overview: Able to recognize the Power Rangers' voices, the Psycho Rangers assume human disguises to try and find them when they least suspect it.

episodes.name: The Enemy Within
episodes.overview: While searching for their Mega Voyager, the Power Rangers prepare for a final showdown with the Psycho Rangers.

episodes.name: Andros and the Stowaway
episodes.overview: On a remote planet, Andros befriends a rapidly-growing baby alien on the run from his cruel master.

episodes.name: Mission to Secret City
episodes.overview: Andros and Carlos are trapped inside Astronema's Secret City forcing Andros to discover untapped powers in his Astro Morpher to save the day.

episodes.name: Ghosts in the Machine
episodes.overview: The Rangers race to stop Astronema from using her new device to turn people into Data Cards.

episodes.name: The Impenetrable Web
episodes.overview: Astronema lures the Rangers into a trap on a distant planet.

episodes.name: A Line in the Sand
episodes.overview: The vehicular monster Takenstein stalks the Power Rangers in a vast desert.

episodes.name: Countdown to Destruction (1)
episodes.overview: Dark Specter's combined armies launch a final all-out assault on the entire universe.

episodes.name: Countdown to Destruction (2)
episodes.overview: With the forces of evil all but triumphant, the Power Rangers make one last desperate attempt to save Zordon.

6.name: In Space
6.overview: After defending the Earth against wave after wave of alien invasions, the Power Rangers finally take the fight to the stars.  With all of their villains united under the banner of the titanic villain Dark Specter, our heroes search the galaxy for their captured mentor Zordon.

episodes.name: Quasar Quest (1)
episodes.overview: An adventurous young man embarks on an epic adventure in space when he sneaks aboard the massive space colony Terra Venture.

episodes.name: Quasar Quest (2)
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Rangers are born as five heroes unite to protect the planet Mirinoi from the villain Furio.

episodes.name: Race to the Rescue
episodes.overview: The Rangers befriend the Galactabeasts - five enormous animals that help them defend Terra Venture from the forces of the evil Scorpius.

episodes.name: Rookie in Red
episodes.overview: Leo adjusts to his responsibilities as a member of the GSA when he forgets to properly lock a weapon storage room on Terra Venture.

episodes.name: Homesick
episodes.overview: A homesick boy who misses Earth helps the Rangers during Furio's sleeping gas attack on Terra Venture.

episodes.name: The Lights of Orion
episodes.overview: The shape-changing monster Mutantrum poses as Mike to lure Leo to the legendary Lights of Orion.

episodes.name: Double Duty
episodes.overview: Battling the Wisewizard, Kendrix meets an actress on a movie set who looks exactly like her.

episodes.name: The Blue Crush
episodes.overview: Kai is smitten by a pretty girl but has little time for romance as the Quake Maker monster attacks Terra Venture with Earthquakes.

episodes.name: The Magna Defender
episodes.overview: The heroic Magna Defender renews his feud with Scorpius' new general Treacheron.

episodes.name: The Sunflower Search
episodes.overview: Seeking vengeance for his son, the Magna Defender battles the Fish Face monster on Terra Venture

episodes.name: Silent Sleep
episodes.overview: Leo and the Magna Defender are forced to work together when the Chillyfish monster freezes the people of Terra Venture.

episodes.name: Orion Rising
episodes.overview: Kendrix and Maya work to escape from a force field created by the monster Destruxo before he can find the Lights of Orion.

episodes.name: Orion Returns
episodes.overview: It's a three-way race between the Power Rangers, the Magna Defender, and Destruxo as the Lights of Orion return.

episodes.name: Shark Attack
episodes.overview: Treacheron turns on Trakeena as the Power Rangers must fight the Shark Brothers without Leo.

episodes.name: Redemption Day
episodes.overview: The Magna Defender struggles to overcome his regrets of the past while protecting Terra Venture.

episodes.name: Destined for Greatness
episodes.overview: Mike returns to Terra Venture and searches for a new role to fight against the Skelekron monster.

episodes.name: Stolen Beauty
episodes.overview: After hearing from her monster that she isn't the prettiest girl in the world, Trakeena orders him to steal the beauty of all the attractive women of Terra Venture. After she tries to trick Mike, he understands what's been going on and destroys her monster, with the Rangers help. Meanwhile, Trakeena has scurried home, but her father has told her it's time for her to go through her full metamorphosis but she refuses and runs away making Scorpius angry.

episodes.name: The Rescue Mission
episodes.overview: A rescue team led by Mike follows a distress call to an abandoned space ship. There they find a spider monster who captures most of the crew. Mike and Leo free the team, and retrieve a mysterious book, just before the ship explodes.

episodes.name: The Lost Galactabeasts (1)
episodes.overview: The treacherous Deviot assists Scorpius by unleashing three lost Galactabeasts to attack Terra Venture.

episodes.name: The Lost Galactabeasts (2)
episodes.overview: The Rangers struggle to free the lost Galactabeasts from Deviot.

episodes.name: Heir to the Throne
episodes.overview: Trakeena escapes the planet Onyx, where she is trained by Villamax. Meanwhile, Deviot sets Scorpius up to be killed by the Rangers. When Trakeena hears of this, she races back to the Scorpion Stinger to assume command, just in time to prevent Deviot from using her coccoon.

episodes.name: An Evil Game
episodes.overview: Trakeena captures Leo to make him pay for killing her father. The two fight one on one, until Deviot's hitmen try to kill Trakeena. She turns the tables on the assassins, and Leo escapes while the villains are distracted.

episodes.name: Memories of Mirinoi
episodes.overview: One of Maya's old friends, Shondra, appears on Terra Venture. Kendrix's suspicions of her are proven to be true, when Maya finds Shondra stealing the Galaxy Book. Shondra reveals herself to be one of Trakeena's monster, and the Rangers destroy her and retrieve the book.

episodes.name: Green Courage
episodes.overview: Holding High Commander Renier hostage, Trakeena demands that Terra Venture send her a mechanic to fix the Scorpion Stinger. Damon volunteers, and while he works on the engine, Leo sneaks in and frees the Commander.

episodes.name: Blue to the Test
episodes.overview: One of Trakeena's monster takes control of Commander Stanton's mind, and has him set Terra Venture on a course towards a star. Only by disregarding the rules and following his instincts is Kai able to discover this plot, free Stanton, and save Terra Venture.

episodes.name: Mean Wheels Mantis
episodes.overview: Leo, Damon, and Kai race the Motor Mantis monster on motorcycles, the prize: Kendrix and Maya!

episodes.name: Loyax’ Last Battle
episodes.overview: Deviot sends the honorable warrior Loyax to destroy the Rangers, but when he meets Maya he questions the honor in his ways.

episodes.name: A Red Romance
episodes.overview: Leo struggles to earn the approval of the brother of the girl he wants to date while trying to save her from Trakeena's latest monster.

episodes.name: The Chameliac Warrior
episodes.overview: The Rangers fight the Chameliac Warrior to save their Galactabeasts.

episodes.name: To the Tenth Power
episodes.overview: Deviot enlists the Psycho Rangers to capture the Galaxy Rangers, prompting Andros and the Space Rangers to travel to Terra Venture to help.

episodes.name: The Power of Pink
episodes.overview: The Space Rangers and Galaxy Rangers unite to help Kendrix against the Pink Psycho Ranger.

episodes.name: Protect the Quasar Saber
episodes.overview: Karone once again assumes the role of Astronema as she risks her life to save the Pink Quasar Saber from falling into the hands of evil.

episodes.name: Facing the Past
episodes.overview: Karone struggles to overcome her evil past as Astronema while adjusting to being the new Pink Galaxy Ranger.

episodes.name: Turn Up the Volume
episodes.overview: Damon competes for the position of chief mechanic. He is beaten by Baxter, who steals his plans to win. Baxter and Damon must then team up to defeat the Decibat monster, by using the machine Damon invented.

episodes.name: Enter the Lost Galaxy
episodes.overview: The Guardian arrives on Terra Venture, to get the Galaxy Book back. Deviot interferes, and the Guardian is killed, passing on the role of guardian to Kai. Deviot gets the book, and transports Terra Venture into the lost galaxy.

episodes.name: Beware the Mutiny
episodes.overview: Terra Venture is greeted in the Lost Galaxy by Captain Mutiny, who the Rangers discover runs a slave camp, and is looking to add the colony's citizens to his work force. Mutiny unleashes the Grunchor monster on Terra Venture, which burrows underground.

episodes.name: Grunchor on the Loose
episodes.overview: The Rangers race to find the Grunchor monster, who is causing massive earthquakes and destruction on the station. He surfaces at the command of Barbarax, and attacks the Rangers, who destroy him with fire.

episodes.name: Until Sunset
episodes.overview: Leo and Damon are captured by Captain Mutiny and hung out to bake in the sun. As they roast, they remember their past adventure as Rangers. The others find them and set them free.

episodes.name: Dream Battle
episodes.overview: Captain Mutiny's sorceress Hexuba uses her magic to cause the Power Rangers to fall into a deep restless sleep.

episodes.name: Hexuba’s Graveyard
episodes.overview: Hexuba resurrects past monsters, and sends them down to Terra Venture. The Rangers wear themselves out battling monster after monster, but Kai travels to the source, a graveyard, and puts an end to Hexuba's voodoo.

episodes.name: Raise the Titanisaur
episodes.overview: Captain Mutiny decides to unleash his most fearsome monster against the Rangers - the Titanisaur. The Rangers and their Megazords must combine all of their powers and give it all they've got to defeat this creature.

episodes.name: Escape the Lost Galaxy
episodes.overview: Mike sacrifices to help Terra Venture escape the Lost Galaxy.

episodes.name: Journey’s End (1)
episodes.overview: Terra Venture discovers a lush green planet to colonize as Trakeena merges with Deviot to become stronger than ever.

episodes.name: Journey’s End (2)
episodes.overview: The Rangers work to evacuate the crew of Terra Venture as Trakeena launches her final assault.

episodes.name: Journey’s End (3)
episodes.overview: Trapped on a desolate Moon in the ruins of Terra Venture, Leo faces Trakeena all alone.

7.name: Lost Galaxy
7.overview: Terra Venture – a space ship so massive it contains a city inside – embarks on an interstellar voyage to settle human pioneers on a distant planet.  A new team of Power Rangers defends the space colony from the alien armies of Trakeena in a saga that will take them to undiscovered worlds and even other galaxies.

episodes.name: Operation Lightspeed
episodes.overview: Five brave young men and women are recruited by the secret agency Lightspeed Rescue to stop a band of demons from destroying Mariner Bay.

episodes.name: Lightspeed Teamwork
episodes.overview: The Rangers deploy the Rescue Bird to evacuate people from a burning building while fighting the lava monster Magmavore.

episodes.name: Trial By Fire
episodes.overview: Carter struggles with leading the Rangers in battle as he recalls a traumatic event from his childhood.

episodes.name: Riding the Edge
episodes.overview: The team rushes to help Kelsey's friend Nancy try to land a space shuttle under attack by Diabolico.

episodes.name: A Matter of Trust
episodes.overview: Dana is trusted with a special assignment by her father.

episodes.name: Wheels of Destruction
episodes.overview: The Rangers and Vypra battle it out in new advanced vehicles.

episodes.name: Cyborg Rangers
episodes.overview: General McKnight tries to replace the Power Rangers with robotic doubles.

episodes.name: Up to the Challenge
episodes.overview: Chad faces a dangerous new opponent secretly in league with Vypra.

episodes.name: Go Volcanic
episodes.overview: Dana faces double trouble when the bus she's on is hijacked and a monster causes a volcano to erupt in Mariner Bay.

episodes.name: Rising from Ashes
episodes.overview: The Power Rangers attempt to rescue Miss Fairweather from an erupting volcano.

episodes.name: From Deep in the Shadows
episodes.overview: The mysterious Titanium Ranger attacks the Power Rangers.

episodes.name: Truth Discovered
episodes.overview: Captain Mitchell is reunited with his long-lost son.

episodes.name: Ryan's Destiny
episodes.overview: Ryan does some soul-searching while Diabolico attacks Mariner Bay.

episodes.name: Curse of the Cobra
episodes.overview: Ryan tries to hide his curse from the team.

episodes.name: Strength of the Sun
episodes.overview: Ryan risks life and limb to overcome his curse and help the Rangers battle Diabolico's monsters.

episodes.name: The Cobra Strikes
episodes.overview: Ryan journeys to an ancient tomb to overcome the curse of the cobra once and for all.

episodes.name: Olympius Ascends
episodes.overview: Impus completes his transformation into Olympius, who has captured four Rangers, and infiltrates the Aquabase by posing as them. His plot is uncovered by Carter, who weakens him by throwing him into water, and frees his friends.

episodes.name: A Face from the Past
episodes.overview: When a monster sets a power plant ablaze, Captain Mitchell jumps into action and braves the fire to rescue a little girl. The incident reveals to Carter that it was Captain Mitchell who has saved him from a fire many years back when he was a child.

episodes.name: The Queen's Return
episodes.overview: The demons perform a ritual to return Queen Bansheera to her bodily form. The Rangers interrupt the ceremony, but only enough to bring back the Queen in a deformed state, for which Olympius swears vengeance. Ryan decides that he will leave the Aquabase to go after the Queen, and promises Dana that he will return.

episodes.name: The Omega Project
episodes.overview: Joel is visiting a young friend, Simon, who invents a telescope to observe outer space. However, Simon discovers that an asteroid is approaching the Earth, which was sent by Olympius to impact Mariner Bay. To stop it, the Rangers initiate the Omega Project, which consists of the Omega Zords - five spacecraft which combine into the Omega Crawler and later the Omega Megazord.

episodes.name: The Fifth Crystal
episodes.overview:
Vypra steals a powerful set of crystals to power a laser which will destroy Mariner Bay. Kelsey teams up with her estranged grandmother to destroy the laser and retrieve the crystals.

This episode was dedicated to Robert L. Manahan, who died on June 30, 2000. He was the voice of Zordon in Mighty Morphin Power Rangers through Power Rangers in Space.

episodes.name: The Chosen Path
episodes.overview: Chad works to regain the respect of his disappointed martial arts instructor.

episodes.name: Yesterday Again
episodes.overview: A simulation goes awry when Carter's day repeats itself, and he uses his knowledge of the future, and his new Mobile Armored Vehicle, to prevent the Rangers' deaths at the hands of Olympius, who attempts to use their own Rescuebird against them.

episodes.name: As Time Runs Out
episodes.overview: The Rangers take the Max Solarzord to space to prevent spores which have attached to them from going off and releasing toxins into the atmosphere. Meanwhile, Loki and Vypra resurrect Diabolico after they are betrayed by Olympius.

episodes.name: In the Freeze Zone
episodes.overview: Freezer captures four Rangers, with only Carter left to face him and Olympius. Olympius has his own problems, as Diabolico returns looking for payback. Bansheera keeps Diabolico in check, and sends her son to get Carter, who defeats Freezer and frees his friends with the new Thermo Blaster.

episodes.name: The Mighty Mega Battles
episodes.overview: Joel becomes jealous when he mistakes Clark, Ms. Fairweather's brother, for her boyfriend. She brought him to the Aquabase to help design the new Mega Battle Armor, which Joel and Chad use to defeat Infinitor. Ms. Fairweather later assures Joel that Clark was just her brother.

episodes.name: The Great Egg Caper
episodes.overview: Jinxer loses an egg containing a powerful monster to a quick witted thief who the Rangers are also after. His plot to hold the egg for ransom backfires when the villains attack him, but he is saved by Kelsey, who discovers the thief to have a heart of gold.

episodes.name: Ocean Blue
episodes.overview: Vypra uses Chad's new love interest, a mermaid named Marina, to lure Chad into a trap. When Marina's life is endangered, Chad summons up the strength and courage to defeat Vypra and Loki and rescue her. The two reunite, but only to part ways soon after.

episodes.name: Trakeena's Revenge (1)
episodes.overview: Trakeena comes to Mariner Bay, prompting the Lost Galaxy Rangers to team up with the Lightspeed Rescue Rangers.

episodes.name: Trakeena's Revenge (2)
episodes.overview: The Lost Galaxy and Lightspeed Rescue Rangers join forces to stop Trakeena from destroying Mariner Bay.

episodes.name: The Last Ranger
episodes.overview: Dana helps her teammates overcome a case of amnesia.

episodes.name: Sorcerer of the Sands
episodes.overview: The Rangers are transported into the monster underworld, where they face invincible dead monsters. They escape with the help of the Sorcerer of the Sands, who Ryan has found in the desert in hopes of discovering a way to imprison the demons. Olympius remains trapped in the underworld, and Diabolico kills the sorcerer in a battle of spells.

episodes.name: Olympius Unbound
episodes.overview: Jinxer manipulates Captain Mitchell into providing Olympius with enough energy to destroy the Rangers after he escapes the underworld. When Ms. Fairweather interrupts the power feed, the star power is destroyed, allowing the Rangers to defeat the demon prince.

episodes.name: Neptune's Daughter
episodes.overview: Marina returns to ask for Chad's help after her father's trident is stolen, which a water demon uses to drain the water from Mariner Bay. Chad recovers the trident, as well as a captive Marina, and safely returns the two to Neptune, the god of the sea.

episodes.name: Web War
episodes.overview: The Arachnor monster traps the Rangers in its web forcing Carter to deploy the Trans Armor Cycle: Mega Armor mode.

episodes.name: In the Limelight
episodes.overview: Dana balances being a glamorous supermodel with her duties as the Pink Ranger.

episodes.name: Wrath of the Queen
episodes.overview: Bansheera unleashes her magnificent power on friend and foe alike.

episodes.name: Rise of the Super Demons
episodes.overview: Olympius and Diabolico join forces prompting the Rangers to risk using the Lifeforce Megazord powered by their own life energy.

episodes.name: The Fate of Lightspeed (1)
episodes.overview: Jinxer launches a crippling attack on the Aquabase.

episodes.name: The Fate of Lightspeed (2)
episodes.overview: The Lightspeed Rescue Rangers take their battle against Queen Bansheera into her very lair.

8.name: Lightspeed Rescue
8.overview: After 5000 years of imprisonment, the demon armies of Diabolico threaten to destroy the human race, prompting a secret government agency called Lightspeed Rescue to recruit a team of heroes to protect the world as the newest Power Rangers.

episodes.name: Force from the Future (1)
episodes.overview: In the year 3000 the evil mutant fugitive Ransik escapes the custody of the elite police force known as Time Force.

episodes.name: Force from the Future (2)
episodes.overview: Traveling back in time in pursuit of Ransik, the Time Force officers meet the distant ancestor of their former leader.

episodes.name: Something to Fight For
episodes.overview: Wes weighs his privileged lifestyle against the responsibilities of joining the Power Rangers Time Force as the new Red Ranger.

episodes.name: Ransik Lives
episodes.overview: Ransik kidnaps Wes and takes over a television station to announce his evil plans to the world.

episodes.name: A Blue Streak
episodes.overview: 31st century champion racecar driver Lucas adjusts to 21st century traffic laws as Trip develops new Vector Cycles for the Rangers.

episodes.name: A Parting of Ways
episodes.overview: Ransik hijacks a bus full of school children and Wes' wealthy father refuses to pay the ransom, prompting Wes to reevaluate his place in the family.

episodes.name: Short-Circuited
episodes.overview: Realizing Circuit is the key to the Rangers summoning their Zords, Nadira plots to capture the Rangers' robotic friend.

episodes.name: Jen's Revenge
episodes.overview: Jen tracks down Fatcatfish, the mutant that she's encountered before. She wants to kill Fatcatfish for personal reasons.

episodes.name: The Time Shadow
episodes.overview: Mr. Collins's company develops a new weapon, the Raimei Destroyer, an armored tank to defend itself against Ransik's attacks. But it's no match for the mutant attacks. Even the Rangers Megazord can't stand up to the latest mutant. In the future, a mysterious figure sends them the Time Shadow.

episodes.name: Future Unknown
episodes.overview: The Rangers try to find some 21st-century weapons to help them. They discover that some technology was developed as a result of Ransik's attacks. Consequently, the future has been altered. This creates doubts for Katie who starts to question their reasons for being in this time. Meanwhile, Frax unleashes a mutant on the city. Now each Ranger must find their own motivation for stopping this latest mutant.

episodes.name: Uniquely Trip
episodes.overview: Trip begins to feel like he's not contributing to the Rangers. He tries to emulate the others in battle, but ends up causing more problems. As Ransik releases a mutant who feeds off energy, Trip realizes how he helps the team in their battles, and finishes building a new weapon for the team.

episodes.name: Worlds Apart
episodes.overview: Wes' dad forms the Silver Guardians, a paramilitary squad to protect the rich from Ransik's gang of mutants.

episodes.name: The Quantum Quest
episodes.overview: On a dig, some researchers discover a metallic object. As word of the discovery spreads, Ransik recognizes the object as the Quantum Controller, and unleashes a mutant to get it for him. Circuit also recognizes the object, and the Rangers try to recover the object before it falls into the wrong hands. As the Rangers fight the mutant, Eric manages to take the controller and hides it away. He then tries to become the Guardian's new leader, but is turned down. So he goes back to where the controller is. The mutant attacks again. As the Rangers fight the mutant, Wes tries to convince Eric to give up the controller, but he ignores him and activates the Quantum Controller, becoming the Quantum Ranger in the process.

episodes.name: Clash for Control (1)
episodes.overview: Even without the Quantum morpher, Ransik wants to possess the Quantasaurus Rex, the Quantum Ranger's megazord. He sends Commandocon to retrieve it. The Rangers try to talk Eric into giving up the morpher, but he refuses. They all witness a time portal opening, realizing that someone is after the Q-Rex, Eric summons the Eagle flyer and enters the portal. Wes jumps onto the flyer.

episodes.name: Clash for Control (2)
episodes.overview: In the past, they try to locate the Q-Rex. But Commandocon gets to it first, takes control of the Q-Rex and journeys back to the 21st century. Eric and Wes follow him back through the time portal. The Q-Rex is rampaging in the city. The Rangers need the Quantum Morpher to get control of the Q-Rex. While Wes tries to talk to Eric, Mr Collins makes the other Rangers an offer to join the Silver Guardians, with his company they could defeat Ransik faster. Will they join the Guardians?

episodes.name: Bodyguard in Blue
episodes.overview: As Dr Zaskins tries to unlock the secrets of the Quantum morpher, he is kidnapped. His daughter, Holly, manages to escape, and tries to hire Lucas as her bodyguard. Lucas is hesitant but then finds out who her father is. While the other Rangers rescue Zaskin, Lucas protects Holly.

episodes.name: The Legend of the Clock Tower
episodes.overview: The Rangers try to fix the clock in the tower, but have no luck. Wes tells them about a ghost that is supposed to inhabit the tower. That night Katie hears a noise, and she investigates. She finds herself in the past, and meets the people from Wes's story. With her help, there's a different ending to the story. Then she wakes up as a mutant attacks. After the battle, she tells her friends about her dream and how the ending had changed, but Wes corrects her and says that's how he had told it, leaving her wondering if it really was a dream.

episodes.name: Trust and Triumph
episodes.overview: Jen tells Wes to guard the back of a bank so the Rangers can cut off Nadira's escape route. But the Guardians show up, and Wes tries to deal with them, giving Nadira a chance to escape. Jen is upset with Wes and says that she can't trust him. Meanwhile, Turtlecon attacks and sends the Rangers to a different dimension and after a short battle with duplicate Ranger, Wes and Jen manage to escape. They have to learn to trust each other if they want to rescue their friends.

episodes.name: Trip Takes a Stand
episodes.overview: Trip stands up to Ransik and Eric to protect a peaceful repentant mutant fugitive.

episodes.name: Quantum Secrets
episodes.overview:
As researchers work on unlocking the secrets of the Quantum Morpher, Ransik releases Conwing to take control of the Q-Rex. Conwing captures Eric, takes his morpher and replicates Eric's voice, which lets him take control of the Q-Rex. Eric finds out where the morpher comes from. The Rangers show up and try to help out but Eric wants to handle it alone. He suddenly gets some help from the future and uses Mega Battle mode. Will Eric reveal the Rangers secrets?

Note: This episode is dedicated to the memory of Minoru Uchiyama, who was the costume designer and make up artist for various Super Sentai series.

episodes.name: Lovestruck Rangers
episodes.overview: The male members of Time Force all seem to be attracted to the same girl for different reasons. When it starts to cause friction in the team, Jen orders them to stop seeing her. Hearing that Wes missed a job, Jen tracks him down and finds that he's still seeing the same girl, who it turns out is a mutant. Now it's up to Jen and Katie to free their teammates from her influence. Jen breaks the mutant's control bracelet and the Rangers capture her after quite long fight.

episodes.name: The Last Race
episodes.overview: Lucas has to attend traffic school after being ticketed for reckless driving (even though the others caused Lucas to be ticketed). Nadira releases Dash, a former racing champion, to be her personal driver. The Rangers arrive, Dash and Lucas recognize each other. Dash had caused a huge accident while street racing and Lucas had to testify against him. Dash challenges him to one last race. If Lucas wins, he promises to accept responsibility for his actions and turn himself in. But Nadira has other plans for him. Ultimately, Dash stops the race when he nearly causes another accident but Nadira forces him to fight. He is defeated and willingly surrenders, but asks Lucas to be the one who refreezes him, which he does.

episodes.name: Full Exposure
episodes.overview: A photographer working for a tabloid is given a new assignment, to take pictures of the Rangers in their civilian guise. He needs help carrying his equipment and hires Katie to help him. His first attempt fails and Katie manages to warn the others. Katie sticks with him so she can keep tabs on him. Meanwhile, Artillicon attacks again and the Rangers attack backfires on them, resulting in them reverting to their civilian identities. As the photographer prepares to sell his pictures, Katie tries to talk him out of it.

episodes.name: Movie Madness (1)
episodes.overview: The heroes are trapped by Ransik's gang in various movie genre dimensions.

episodes.name: Movie Madness (2)
episodes.overview: The Rangers work to escape various movie genre dimensions.

episodes.name: Time Force Traitor
episodes.overview: A former Time Force officer, Steelix, Jen's old Time Force partner, seeks revenge on Jen for getting him locked up. He steals her morpher, fights her on her own, then turns her insane. Wes breaks Jen out of the spell, and all of the Rangers defeat Steelix after the long fight.

episodes.name: Frax's Fury
episodes.overview: Frax's origin is revealed as he finally has enough of Ransik's abuse.

episodes.name: Dawn of Destiny
episodes.overview: The time travelers' actions in the present begin to change the future as a previously dead ally from the past returns.

episodes.name: Fight Against Fate
episodes.overview: As Mr Collins lies gravelly injured in the hospital, Wes runs his company. Alex leads the Rangers in a battle against a new powerful robot. But his attitude and leadership style create friction within the group.

episodes.name: Destiny Defeated
episodes.overview: Wes refuses to acknowledge the idea of destiny and decides to choose his own path in life.

episodes.name: Undercover Rangers
episodes.overview: Jen and Wes go undercover to investigate a shady gym in Silver Hills.

episodes.name: Beware the Knight
episodes.overview: While returning to the Clock Tower with some pizzas, Trip encounters a mysterious knight on a horse. The mysterious knight vanishes into the forest. The knight is after something that is guarded by a dragon. Debut of the Fire Battle Armor.

episodes.name: Time for Lightspeed
episodes.overview: Vypra aligns with Ransik in order to release a super demon to destroy the world. The Time Force Rangers team up with Carter Grayson and the rest of the Lightspeed Rangers to combat this threat.

episodes.name: Reflections of Evil
episodes.overview: A mutant named Miracon transports the Rangers into a mirror world, where the Rangers must escape from by destroying new and old mutant enemies.

episodes.name: Nadira's Dream Date
episodes.overview: Lucas writes a romantic poem about his first love, his first racecar, and during a battle against Ransik's forces, he unknowingly drops it. Nadira picked it up and believed that Lucas has romantic feelings for her, leading Ransik to warn him to treat his daughter right or face his wrath.

episodes.name: Circuit Unsure
episodes.overview: Circuit's memories are erased by a member of Time Force in the future causing Circuit to doubt his ability to help the Rangers.

episodes.name: A Calm Before the Storm
episodes.overview: With Ransik's mutants depleted, the Rangers ponder their past and future as Rangers. Meanwhile, Frax's new robot terrorizes the city, but is destroyed by Eric and the Q-Rex.

episodes.name: The End of Time (1)
episodes.overview: The Rangers receive a chilling warning from the future as Ransik reprograms Frax and Nadira questions her life as a super villainess.

episodes.name: The End of Time (2)
episodes.overview: Wes sends the Time Force Rangers back to the future as Frax and his giant robot launch a devastating attack on Silver Hills that no one may survive.

episodes.name: The End of Time (3)
episodes.overview: Jen and her teammates disobey orders in order to go back in time to rescue Wes and stop Ransik at any cost.

9.name: Time Force
9.overview: Fugitive mutants from the distant future escape to the present to unleash a wave of crime against a helpless world but the futuristic police force known as the Power Rangers Time Force travel across time to save the past, present, and future.

episodes.name: Lionheart
episodes.overview: A young man raised in the jungle travels to the city of Turtle Cove and discovers an island - home to legendary beasts from an ancient civilization - floating in the sky above the city.

episodes.name: Darkness Awakening
episodes.overview: Cole seeks to reason with the Orgs while Jindrax and Toxica discover that after 3000 years the Master Org has returned to Earth again.

episodes.name: Click, Click, Zoom
episodes.overview: Master Org gives Toxica and Jindrax a pep talk in preparation for his next dastardly plan. Cole reads Taylor's Ranger rule book, but says there should only be one rule: teamwork.

episodes.name: Never Give Up
episodes.overview: Max reads the newspaper and suggests that he and Danny check out the haunted temple to see if it has an org. Danny's mind is elsewhere, though, as he has his eyes on Kendall, whom he has a crush on.

episodes.name: Ancient Awakening
episodes.overview: Alyssa starts a day at school on an archeological dig. While snooping around, she finds a glowing Wild Force emblem inside a cave. Later, she grabs Princess Shayla and Cole to help her check it out.

episodes.name: Wishes on the Water
episodes.overview: Alyssa reads a story to Max and Danny about a creature in Turtle Lake that can grant wishes. Max falls asleep and has a short dream about the megazord getting defeated.

episodes.name: The Bear Necessities
episodes.overview: When jogging, Taylor stops by at the airport and remembers when she first came to the Animarium. She then meets two boys: wearing black and white, running from a security guard.

episodes.name: Soul Searching
episodes.overview: The rangers learn of a magical bird called the Soul Bird in the forest that can heal the Wild Zords. Cole thinks it may be able to heal the Red Lion, so the Rangers head off to find it.

episodes.name: Soul Bird Salvation
episodes.overview: Master Org's old bodyguard Retinax fights the Power Rangers to restore his lost honor.

episodes.name: Curse of the Wolf
episodes.overview: Master Org releases the General Org Nayzor, who finds and releases another Duke Org - Zen-Aku. Zen-Aku utterly defeats the Rangers in battle, and steals the Elephant zord from Alyssa.

episodes.name: Battle of the Zords
episodes.overview: An injured Alyssa is tended to by Zen-Aku, after she is attacked by Toxica and Jindrax. Zen-Aku summons his own Dark Wild Zords to battle the Rangers' Wild Zords.

episodes.name: Predazord, Awaken
episodes.overview: After defeating the runaway Bus org, the Rangers face Zen-Aku who defeats Cole easily in a brief battle, he also combines his Dark Wild Zords into the Predazord, and steals the Giraffe Power Animal from them.

episodes.name: Revenge of Zen-Aku
episodes.overview: Zen-Aku frees Motorcycle Org, and kidnaps Princess Shayla. Shayla's necklace brings back vague memories for Zen-Aku. The Rangers battle Motorcycle Org and Zen-Aku, and get back the Princess. Taylor is defeated by Zen-Aku, who steals the Bear animal crystals.

episodes.name: Identity Crisis
episodes.overview: As Zen-Aku begins to remember his true past, Nayzor plants a bug in his head, which convinces him that he is pure evil, making him an even more dangerous threat to the Rangers.

episodes.name: The Ancient Warrior
episodes.overview: The ancient Animus intervenes to reveal Zen-Aku's true identity - Merrick, the ancient warrior who defeated Master Org by using the cursed wolf mask. By defeating the Predazord with new zords, the Rangers break the curse, returning Merrick back to normal.

episodes.name: The Lone Wolf
episodes.overview: After a failed attempt to retrieve the stolen Animal Crystals, Merrick must fight the Quadra Org, who was created with the power of the crystals. With the Rangers tied up, Merrick battles on his own, until his Wild Zords return to him and give him the power to morph into the Lunar Wolf Ranger.

episodes.name: Power Play
episodes.overview: Toxica powers herself up into the newest General Org - Necronomica. Merrick helps the Rangers defeat her with his newest vehicle - the Wolf Savage Cycle.

episodes.name: Secrets and Lies
episodes.overview: Signal Org makes Cole lose his memory. He ends up on a farm, and is eventually found by the Rangers and returned to normal just in time to defeat Signal Org. Also, Alyssa discovers that Cole's parents have been presumed dead.

episodes.name: The Tornado Spin
episodes.overview: Bowling Org makes Max learn a new bowling technique the tornado spin. To learn the move, he must convince his old bowling coach to regain his will to bowl.

episodes.name: Three's a Crowd
episodes.overview: Danny competes for Kendall's affection while the Rangers try to find Wedding Dress Org and his captives. Kendall discovers that Danny is the Black Ranger, and inspires him to single handedly turn the tide against the Org. In the end, Danny's life doesn't allow them to be together.

episodes.name: A Father's Footsteps
episodes.overview: Alyssa's father is in town, and calls Alyssa for lunch. Samurai Org stirs up trouble, and Alyssa must recall her father's training to defeat him.

episodes.name: Sing Song
episodes.overview: To defeat Tombstone Org, who is powered by six Org spirits, the Rangers need the help of the Deer Zord. To get the Deer to help them, Shayla and Merrick must sing for him to make him happy again.

episodes.name: The Wings of Animaria
