When Porcupongo appears again, the boys go after him while Lily and Fran argue, eventually making Lily turn back into herself and join the fight against Porcupongo and defeat him once and for all.

episodes.name: Friends Don't Fade Away
episodes.overview: After battling with Dai Shi, RJ cannot control his Animal Spirit and goes insane. He becomes a wolf and has to be restrained. Fran then places her palm on his wolf hand he returns to his human form, She then reminds him to ask his friends for help rather than run away. RJ regains control of himself and becomes the Wolf Ranger.

episodes.name: No "I" in Leader
episodes.overview: Now that RJ has joined the team as the Wolf Ranger, Casey is beginning to doubt himself as the leader of the Rangers. Meanwhile, Grizzaka releases a pair of stronger Shadow Guards who give the Rangers a tough time. Master Mao's spirit visits Jarrod and unknowingly sends him on a quest for the Rhino Nexus.

episodes.name: True Friends, True Spirits
episodes.overview: After R.J. saves Flit, the little fly becomes an unwanted friend, but when R.J. is in trouble only Flit can save him. Meanwhile, Grizzaka releases an evil spirit making R.J. lose control of his spirit again.

episodes.name: Path of the Rhino
episodes.overview: Dominic was sent out by Master Mao to find purpose for his life. He finds out that RJ and the others are really Rangers and he wants to join them. He now knows that this is his purpose in life. Casey is dubious but Dominic proves he has the spirit of the Rhino. Dominic becomes the Rhino Ranger.

episodes.name: Dash for the Dagger
episodes.overview: Dominic and Theo depart for the Control Dagger, but are side tracked with the attack of Whirnado. Meanwhile, Dai Shi returns to the temple where he is imprisoned. Camille attempts to take the Control Dagger which is the only way into the Rhino Nexus.

episodes.name: Race to the Nexus
episodes.overview: With the Control Dagger in hand, Dai Shi aims to unlock the Nexus for himself. The Overlords refuse to let such power fall into the hands of the Rangers or Dai Shi. Having searched all his life for his destiny, Dominic isn't about to let the Overlords, or Dai Shi stand in his way. With the help of his friends, Dominic is able to unlock the power of the Rhino Nexus and summons the Rhino Steel Zord to transform into Rhino Pride Megazord and destroy Carnisoar.

episodes.name: Arise the Crystal Eyes
episodes.overview: The Rangers learn about the Crystal Eyes, while Dai Shi sends Camille to steal the Crystal Eyes so he can revive the Phantom Generals, while the Rangers (minus Casey) fight Grizzaka. Casey and Jarrod fight over the Crystal Eyes, while Jellica attempts to steal them. Casey comes to the aid of his friends after Dai Shi warns him that they stand no chance against Grizzaka without him. With Casey's added power they finally manage to destroy Grizzaka.

episodes.name: Fear and the Phantoms
episodes.overview: Jellica releases the Phantom Beasts by the crystal eyes, who destroy her and swear allegiance to Dai Shi. Using their power, Dai Shi allows the Phantom Beasts to kidnap the 3 masters, who are used to create the Spirit Rangers.

episodes.name: Blue Ranger, Twin Danger
episodes.overview: With the masters in their possession, the Phantoms have a new weapon, the Spirit Rangers. Meanwhile, Theo's twin brother Luen (Aljin Abella in a dual role) shows up and causes trouble at JKP. One of the Phantom Beasts begins capturing the Rangers within mirror-like discs but mistakingly captures Luen believing him to be Theo. Theo fights the phantom and manages to free all of the Rangers and Luen who learns of his brother's secret of being a Ranger. The Phantom Beast is then destroyed by the ranger's combined might. Later RJ is psychically contacted by his father to help in defeating the Spirit Rangers.

episodes.name: One Last Second Chance
episodes.overview: By redirecting the Claw Cannon to cancel out the Spirit Rangers, RJ accidentally seals his father Master Finn inside one of the Crystal Eyes. Unidoom attempts to throw it into the ocean, but Flit gives it to RJ and RJ brings his father back. They free Masters Swoop & Phant and the Jungle Fury Rangers & Spirit Rangers unite to destroy Unidoom.

episodes.name: Don't Blow That Dough
episodes.overview: Casey, Theo, Dominick and Lily are trapped inside R.J.'s televisions and put into a gameshow/clipshow called Blow That Dough against three former Rinshi Beasts. Dominick, Theo and Lily lose, but Casey manages to win, and when R.J. sends the Morphers, manages to end the game. This episode served as a recap on the previous episodes in Jungle Fury

episodes.name: Tigers Fall, Lions Rise
episodes.overview: Casey and the others fight Whiger and the other Phantom Beast Generals who have given Camille their power and the Phoenix Spirit, and Dai Shi the Griffin Spirit, and made him their king. Whiger steals Casey's Tiger Spirit and the Rangers are easily defeated without his help. When Whiger attacks again Casey goes to Jungle Master Mode to help save the others and his martial arts students, powering the Claw Cannon with a student's Tiger Spirit. Whiger is defeated by the Megazords and flees.

episodes.name: The Spirit of Kindness
episodes.overview: Whiger was only able to steal the Tiger Spirit from Casey, but not destroy Casey. For his failure, Dai Shi strips him of his power and he is to fade away. Casey shows his kindness to Whiger even though they were just battling. Whiger rethinks which side he should be on. He helps Casey save his friends who have been captured along with all the other people in giant rattraps.Together they defeat Camille but Whiger fades to nothing after using up the last of his powers. With the Rangers re-united they destroy the two phantom beasts behind the plot with their animal spirits and afterwards Casey acknowledges that they couldn't have won without Whiger. Later Snapper and Scorch begin to scheme of getting rid of Camille.

episodes.name: Maryl and the Monkeys
episodes.overview: Camille steals a potion from Maryl with the ability to clone Monkeys. She and Dai Shi give it to the Monkey Phantom Beast Warrior Grinder, and uses it to unleash clones of itself throughout the city. Dominic soon destroys Grinder. Dai Shi also realizes that Scorch and Snapper conspired against Camille and stopped her successful plan.

episodes.name: To Earn Your Stripes
episodes.overview: RJ takes Casey, Theo, and Lily back to the Pai Zhua temple for the final test before they earn the rank of Pai Zhua Master... defeating Masters Finn, Swoop and Phant in battle. Although Theo and Lily pass and earn their Master's stripes, Casey fails and, feeling dejected, goes out on his own. Meanwhile Dai Shi starts to lose control over Jarrod as he struggles to break free so Scorch and Snapper send Sonimax, Osirus, and Lepus to destroy Camille because they think she is the cause of it. Casey witnesses Jarrod saving Camille at the last minute and sees that there is some good left in Jarrod. In the end Jarrod gains control long enough to destroy Sonimax and Osirus while the Rangers use their Megazords to destroy Lepus. Dai Shi manages to regain control and Casey, although certain that Jarrod still exists inside Dai Shi, still needs to work out why he failed his test to earn the rank of Master.

episodes.name: Path of the Righteous
episodes.overview: Casey is convinced there is good left in Jarrod, enough to break Dai Shi's control, but the others doubt him knowing that even before he was possessed, Jarrod was a bully who went against those weaker than he was. Undeterred by his friends' doubts and Master Mao's orders not to pursue the issue, he faces Dai Shi at his lair to bring out the goodness in Jarrod. After a hard battle, Casey allows Dai Shi to destroy him and, as a result, Jarrod expels him before he can strike. The two leave the temple along with Camille, who also rebels against Dai Shi to protect Jarrod. The three then leave and are attacked by Scorch and Snapper. The other Rangers show up, and Jarrod and Camille join forces with them to defeat the two Phantom Generals. Scorch becomes a giant, then gets defeated by the Stampede Formation, including Jarrod and Camille's spirit beasts. Casey, for acting on his own instincts instead of copying his friends, finally earns his Master stripes while Jarrod runs off, feeling guilty over the trouble he's caused and the evil he unleashed...

episodes.name: Now the Final Fury
episodes.overview: Scorch is back again with an army of Rinshis invading the city. Dai Shi now has enough power to open a portal to the spirit world and brings back all of his fallen army. The Rangers are soon joined by all of the masters and the Spirit Rangers and are able to destroy all of the revived villains as well as Scorch. Furious, Dai Shi finally reveals his true form (a gigantic hydra-like dragon) and targets the Red Ranger. Jarrod tries to shake the conviction in his heart, but Camille decides to join the Rangers. RJ and Dominic form the WolfPride and Rhino Steel Megazords, but are defeated. Then Jarrod appears and tells Dai- Shi that he was wrong of saying he didn't have the lion's heart, then Jarrod attacked and weakened Dai-Shi with his Zocato power. Master Mao state that only the three chosen ones can destroy Dai Shi for good. "A Pai Zhua Master doesn't ask, he knows. There is a higher level of animal spirits. One that has never been reached before by student or Master. It's time to push beyond the possible, to our highest potential." Then Casey Lily and Theo launch a Big sun blast towards Dai-Shi which destroys him. After that, Casey starts to teach at the academy with Jarrod and Camille starting all over again in it, Theo finally asks Lily for a date, RJ starts working with Flit, now human again, Dom goes on a tour with Fran.

16.name: Jungle Fury
16.overview: When the ancient evil spirit Dai Shi returns to wipe out all humans, a trio of teenagers must learn secret kung fu styles based on the world's most ferocious jungle animals to become Power Rangers and save the world.

episodes.name: The Road to Corinth
episodes.overview: The Venjix Computer Network is attempting to conquer and lay ruin to the entire planet, and the human race has retreated into the environmentally shielded domed city of Corinth to protect itself from destruction. There, an elite force of Rangers is assembled in order to protect the city and battle the attacking machine army bent on world domination.

episodes.name: Fade to Black
episodes.overview: As Venjix grows stronger, it becomes clear that the Rangers need more than three operators to defend the city. Summer suggests that Dillon be the new Black Ranger, but with him part-machine and part-human, no one knows what side he's really on.

episodes.name: Rain
episodes.overview: Dillon goes through a series of tests to see if he even is Ranger material, but the real test comes when he is faced with the choice of seeking out his past or helping the Rangers as promised.

episodes.name: Go for the Green
episodes.overview: When Ziggy is charged with finding the new Green Ranger, he finds the perfect candidate in Tenaya 7, until he realizes she's a machine working for Venjix!

episodes.name: Handshake
episodes.overview: When Dillon struggles to activate the invincibility mode of his suit, he challenges Dr. K to come out from behind their protective screen.

episodes.name: Ranger Green
episodes.overview: Ziggy's recruitment as Ranger Green is put into question when parts of his shady past are revealed. Should the Rangers work with someone who is hated by all seven of Corinth's cartels?

episodes.name: Ranger Red
episodes.overview: Scott is flooded with memories of his brother when he returns to Marcus' crash site in order to retrieve an over thruster core the Rangers need for the new Megazord configuration.

episodes.name: Ranger Yellow (1)
episodes.overview: Mr. & Mrs. Landsdown suddenly reappear in Summer's life, intent on making their daughter live up to her promise to marry into a wealthy family. Once married, Summer will receive the black diamond, the family heirloom that Venjix plans on using to bring destruction to Corinth.

episodes.name: Ranger Yellow (2)
episodes.overview: Diamonds and pretty dresses are no longer important to Summer, who finds her true meaning in what she does with the Rangers.

episodes.name: Ranger Blue
episodes.overview: A malfunction in his Time Manipulation Burst causes Flynn to be sidelined as the other Rangers face off against Tenaya 7 and her Grinders. While waiting for Doctor K to come up with a solution, Flynn looks back on his life leading up to Venjix's attack and how he came to be the Blue Ranger.

episodes.name: Doctor K
episodes.overview: While attempting to overcome a power problem with the Rangers' new zord configuration, Doctor K is haunted by memories of her childhood being held at the "Alphabet Soup" think tank and a terrible mistake for which she has tried to make up for.

episodes.name: Blitz
episodes.overview: Dillon has a dream about his past when the Rangers are called into action. Venjix sends multiple monsters, wearing the Rangers down, and Dillon must make an important decision when he confronts the monster that has his stolen memories. He decides to keep his new memories and forget everything.

episodes.name: Brother’s Keeper
episodes.overview: Tenaya 7 implants a remote device on Dillon's back of his neck which makes him fall under the control of Venjix and makes his bionic implants begin to take over his body. When he tries to leave the city, Dillon finds himself chained by Scott, leaving the rest of the Rangers to seek out the means to help him.

episodes.name: Embodied
episodes.overview: Dillon seeks to find more about his past by traveling to Omega City with the other Rangers in the GO-ONGER vehicle. They are sidetracked when Venjix downloads himself into a Generation 13 Attack Bot. When things look bad for the Rangers, two new and unknown Rangers appear to help. They then disappear, leaving the five Rangers in wonder of their identities.

episodes.name: Ghosts
episodes.overview: The Rangers arrive at Omega City only to discover it was all a trap set by Venjix. In the midst of trying to escape, they are ambushed and overwhelmed by Venjix forces, but are saved by Rangers Gold and Silver who, this time, fight off their assailants in person. The seven Rangers then return to Corinth, where Rangers Gold and Silver finally reveal themselves as Gem and Gemma, long lost friends of Dr. K from the Alphabet Soup facility.

episodes.name: In or Out
episodes.overview: Scott decides to join Gem and Gemma in a more offensive approach in the battle against Venjix. Colonel Truman defaults to his usual "defend the city" tactics and ends up trapping everyone inside while a Venjix bot sucks all the air out of the city. The remaining Rangers make a deadly escape from Corinth and regroup with Scott in order to save the city.

episodes.name: Prisoners
episodes.overview: Dillon hears Gem & Gemma humming a tune identical to the one from his pocket watch. They inform him that they learned it from a blind girl they befriended in a Venjix work camp, and that the tune came from a pocketwatch belonging to the girl's brother Dillon, convinced that his sister is still there, mounts a rescue attempt with the help of Summer and Ziggy while Scott and Flynn attempt to hold off a dangerous new attack bot. Dr. K and the Rangers learn that Venjix is building a doomsday weapon, and must venture back to the facility to destroy it.

episodes.name: Belly of the Beast
episodes.overview: The Rangers must return to the factory where the doomsday device is being built. Dillon attempts to find his sister before it's too late. Dillon discovers that he, Summer, Gem & Gemma are in his sister's cell. Summer finds the key that belonged to Dillon's sister at Venjix factory that matches Dillon's key.

episodes.name: Threes a Crowd
episodes.overview: Gem & Gemma's "blow things up and ask questions later" motto is getting quite out of hand. They follow a trail they think might lead to the Venjix Palace and end up walking right into a trap. They must learn to work together with the other Rangers as a team and in turn form a new Megazord configuration called the SkyRev Megazord.

episodes.name: Heroes Among Us
episodes.overview: In an effort to impress his father, Scott makes a reckless trip out to the wasteland. He and Gem stumble upon human prisoners and their field trip turns into a rescue mission. Venjix test-drives his new and improved robotic form. His new body doesn't hold up very well against the Rangers. Scott talks to Dillon about the Venjix Prisoners Camp where humans are infected with the Venjix virus, and Grinders make human hybrids like Dillon, his sister & the other at the Venjix Palace.

episodes.name: Not So Simple
episodes.overview: For the first time, Gem and Gemma split up on something. Gemma believes in what Flynn can do. Together, they work on a wheelzord on the side. With all their resources used up, Dr. K has to trust the untested technology and they use it to destroy the latest attack bot.

episodes.name: The Dome Dolls
episodes.overview: A Chemical Attack Bot attacks the city and puts all men fast asleep. Now, the women of Corinth, led by Summer, all have to work together and save the day. Dr. K works on an antidote to awaken the men of Corinth City.

episodes.name: And… Action
episodes.overview: For the first time ever join Ziggy as he takes you behind the scenes & bloopers of Power Rangers. See how explosions and stunts are really done, as well as the funny moments that don’t make it into the episode, but keep the Power Ranger set a lively place to work as a Ranger. The Rangers & Dr. K are sitting on the couch to watch their episode.

episodes.name: Ancient History
episodes.overview: Untested technology is found in an Alphabet Soup dumping ground. Colonel Truman tries to keep the technology from Venjix and comes across a video log that pins Dr. K responsible for the start of Venjix. Colonel Truman wants to arrest Dr. K. but if he does, then she wouldn’t be able to help the Rangers with the dangerous Paleomax technology.

episodes.name: Key to the Past
episodes.overview: It dawns on Dillon that the two keys to his musical pocketwatch fit together to play another tune -- the same one that Tenaya 7 whistles. Tenaya 7 is hit by memories of her past. She does some investigating on her own and finds out what really happened to her. Dillon finds out Tenaya 7 is his long lost sister.

episodes.name: Beyond a Doubt
episodes.overview: Tenaya 7 & Dillon go to Venjix palace to retrieve codes to stop an Attack Bot. Dillon is left wondering which side she is on when she turns him into Venjix. With the stolen codes, Dr. K is able to configure the RPM Ultrazord. Kilobyte captures Tenaya 7 before she can reunite with the Rangers.

episodes.name: Control-Alt-Delete
episodes.overview: Dillon's search for Tenaya is put on hold when Scott is in trouble. Scott was shot with a key that allows Shifter to control him. The Rangers do their best to save their leader when they come face to face with Tenaya 15. She has been reprogrammed with one mission: Serve Venjix. Dr. K makes a gun whose shots can make Tenaya susceptible to mind control.

episodes.name: Run Ziggy Run
episodes.overview: It's time for Ziggy to pay back the $5 million he owes Fresno Bob. Tenaya 15 makes a deal with Fresno Bob to give him Ziggy in exchange for a certain case. Instead, she double-crosses Fresno Bob and Ziggy ends up saving him. The Rangers deploy Dr. K's Rail Saber weapon against the latest Attack Bot. Fresno Bob and Ziggy are now even.

episodes.name: If Venjix Won
episodes.overview: Ziggy and Doctor K are accidentally teleported into a distant cave outside of Corinth. The remaining Rangers need to find out the password to Dr. K's computer and retrieve them, but their efforts instead triggers a time capsule recording compiled by Dr K, to be played only if Venjix attained absolute victory.

episodes.name: End Game
episodes.overview: Venjix’s end game is about to reveal itself. Every Attack Bot has been a calculating step closer to his plan. The city is filled with hybrids just like Dillon. Venjix is going to activate them all and Corinth will be brought down.

episodes.name: Danger and Destiny (1)
episodes.overview: When the magnetic blast goes off and all the electricity goes out in Corinth, Venjix moves to take the city.

episodes.name: Danger and Destiny (2)
episodes.overview: The Rangers race to insert a virus into Venjix before he takes over Corinth.

17.name: R.P.M.
17.overview: In a bleak near future, the Venjix Computer Network and its robot armies have almost completely conquered the world.  In the dome-shielded city of Corinth, a group of heroes equipped with high tech Racing Performance Machines fight a desperate battle for survival as the Power Rangers RPM.

episodes.name: Origins (1)
episodes.overview: As invasions from the Netherworld increase, the Red Ranger unites a new team of Samurai Rangers to meet the rising threat.

episodes.name: Origins (2)
episodes.overview: As the teens continue their transition into their new secret lives as Samurai Rangers, Emily reveals a surprising truth about herself.

episodes.name: The Team Unites
episodes.overview: Mike figures out the hard way what it means to be a Samurai Ranger after a Nighlok attacks him and his friends.

episodes.name: Deal With a Nighlok
episodes.overview: The Rangers step in when a devious Nighlok tricks a young boy into giving up on his baseball dreams.

episodes.name: Day Off
episodes.overview: Struggling to master a secret power disc, Jayden foregoes a trip with the others to an amusement park where the rest of the team encounters the evil Nighlok Dreadhead.

episodes.name: Sticks and Stones
episodes.overview: When a Nighlok who uses insults as a physical weapon attacks the Rangers, only Emily is unaffected. To help her teammates, she explains how difficult events in life become an opportunity to grow stronger.

episodes.name: A Fish Out Of Water
episodes.overview: Kevin is assigned the crucial task of catching the elusive SwordfishZord in order to save the other Rangers who have been incapacitated by the stench of the Nighlok Yamiror's breath.

episodes.name: There Go the Brides
episodes.overview: Dayu crosses into the mortal world to cause misery by kidnapping brides on their wedding day.

episodes.name: I've Got A Spell On Blue
episodes.overview: A Nighlok uses mind control powers to force Kevin to fight against his fellow Rangers.

episodes.name: Forest for the Trees
episodes.overview: After Mike goes rogue in battle, Mentor takes Mike's Samuraizer away until he learns a deeper lesson about the nature of the Green Ranger's Symbol Power.

episodes.name: Test of the Leader
episodes.overview: A Nighlok is sent to stop the Red Ranger from using his special power to seal Master Xandred in the Netherworld forever, but their duel is interrupted by the mysterious Deker.

episodes.name: Jayden's Challenge
episodes.overview: Jayden leaves the Shiba house hoping to keep the other Rangers out of harm's way, but when a powerful Nighlok attacks, Jayden finally accepts the fact that he needs his team to fulfill his role as the leader of the Samurai Rangers.

episodes.name: Unexpected Arrival
episodes.overview: A traveling fisherman named Antonio arrives and claims to be the sixth Samurai Ranger.

episodes.name: Room for One More
episodes.overview: Jayden's childhood friend and self-made Samurai Antonio struggles to be accepted by the team as the Gold Ranger.

episodes.name: The Blue and the Gold
episodes.overview: As Antonio attempts to gain Kevin's respect as a true Samurai, Octoroo devises a plan to create a stronger portal between the Netherworld and Earth via a secret ancient well.

episodes.name: Team Spirit
episodes.overview: The Rangers must defeat the evil Splitface who steals people's spirits including the Yellow Rangers before they fall into an eternal sleep.

episodes.name: The Tengen Gate
episodes.overview: Jayden is poisoned by Octoroo during his attempt to discover the Red Ranger's sealing symbol, which can lock away Master Xandred forever.

episodes.name: Boxed In
episodes.overview: With Jayden kidnapped by Deker, the other Rangers must summon the strength to fight a mutant Nighlok without their leader.

episodes.name: Broken Dreams
episodes.overview: When the Gold and Pink Ranger fall under the spell of a dream-inducing Nighlok, the other Rangers must enter the Dream World to save them.

episodes.name: The Ultimate Duel
episodes.overview: The Rangers try to finish off the dream monster Rhinosnorus while Jayden and Deker finally face off in their ultimate duel.

episodes.name: Party Monsters
episodes.overview: Halloween is every Nighlok's favorite day of the year so the creepiest creatures from the Netherworld are just dying to get into the scariest party ever and trade war stories about their battles with the Samurai Power Rangers.

episodes.name: Clash of the Red Rangers
episodes.overview: The Samurai Rangers team up with the mysterious RPM Ranger Red to fight off dual threats from Master Xandred's Mooger army and a robotic supervillain from the RPM Ranger's dimension.

episodes.name: Christmas Together, Friends Forever
episodes.overview: Twas the night before Christmas and all through the Shiba House the teens reflect on their first year together as a team and as friends.

18.name: Samurai
18.overview: A new generation of Power Rangers must master the ancient Symbols of Samurai Power which give them control over the elements of Fire, Water, Sky, Forest, and Earth.  Under the guidance of their all-knowing mentor and the aid of their devoted animal Zords, they battle the dark forces of the Netherworld and a mysterious Warrior bent on destruction.

episodes.name: Super Samurai
episodes.overview: The Rangers discover that cracks in the earth are now allowing pools of Sanzu River water to seep into our world from the Netherworld and that a mutated Nighlok is using the evil water to keep from drying out as it wreaks havoc throughout the city.

episodes.name: Shell Game
episodes.overview: The Rangers struggle to find a way to defeat a Nighlok with an apparently indestructible shell without the help of Antonio, who has unknowingly lost his Samurai Morpher and cannot be reached. Meanwhile, Bulk and Spike find Antonio's Morpher, but think it's a phone that they must return to the original owner.

episodes.name: Trading Places
episodes.overview: It's mixed-up mayhem when the Rangers encounter Switchbeast, a Nighlok who can trap people's spirits inside common objects. When the monster does this to four of the Rangers, Mike and Emily must figure out how to defeat him on their own.

episodes.name: Something Fishy
episodes.overview: After Antonio develops an unusual fear of fish that leaves him unable to be the Gold Ranger, his teammates rally to help him overcome it. Meanwhile, a mysterious and powerful new enemy arrives to help Master Xandred in his quest to flood the earth.

episodes.name: The Rescue
episodes.overview: Octoroo, with the help of the Nighlok Eyescar, kidnaps Antonio and Mentor to use as bait in order to lead the rest of the Rangers into a Mooger trap.

episodes.name: The Bullzord
episodes.overview: A daring boy named Cody unlocks an ancient seal, releasing an enormous BullZord, the very first Samurai Zord, which rampages across the countryside. The Power Rangers must fight to save the city by capturing the beast and taming it to serve as their newest Megazord.

episodes.name: He Ain't Heavy Metal, He's My Brother
episodes.overview: When Mia's younger brother comes to town to try and convince her to sing lead in his band, the reunion is anything but sweet music. Meanwhile, Serrator once again attacks the city.

episodes.name: Kevin's Choice
episodes.overview: When a Nighlok eats his Samuraizer, Kevin is unable to help the team defeat the beast, at the same time that he is missing his old life as a competitive swimmer. Meanwhile, Dayu and Deker make a deal with the evil Serrator.

episodes.name: Runaway Spike
episodes.overview: While the Rangers battle a crafty Nighlok who creates mirror images of himself to confuse them, Spike realizes that one of the duties of being a Samurai is to share in the responsibilities of day-to-day life and sets off to find a job so he can help pay the rent on his Uncle Bulk's clubhouse.

episodes.name: The Strange Case of the Munchies
episodes.overview: Emily has a crisis in confidence, just as the other Rangers are affected by a Nighlok's evil black sand, which sends them into a desperate hunger/thirst mode. While Emily and Mentor Ji struggle to manage the hungry Rangers and defeat the Nighlok, Bulk and Spike find Mia's wallet and head to the Shiba House to return it.

episodes.name: A Sticky Situation
episodes.overview: After a Nighlok glues their hands together, Kevin and Mike learn that working as a team doesn't just mean sharing their strengths; it's knowing when they need to ask for help with their weaknesses as well.

episodes.name: Trust Me
episodes.overview: Serrator takes the first step in his mysterious master plan to seize the earth by clouding the minds of the people of the island Monalua, spreading paranoia throughout the residents. To stop Serrator, the Rangers will need a special new weapon, the Bullzooka!

episodes.name: The Master Returns
episodes.overview: As Jayden struggles with his sudden doubts on whether or not he has what it takes to be the Red Ranger, Master Xandred demands Serrator return Dayu's Harmonium, prompting Serrator to reveal his true intentions.

episodes.name: A Crack In The World
episodes.overview: The Rangers discover that Serrator's recent attacks have an ulterior motive -- to crack open the earth and let the Sanzu flood it and thereby become ruler of both worlds.

episodes.name: Trickster Treat
episodes.overview: Halloween gets spooktacular when an evil Nighlok invades the Samurai Rangers' dreams and turns them into nightmares.

episodes.name: Stroke of Fate
episodes.overview: When Serrator asks Deker to fulfill the final piece of his destructive plans, Antonio begs Deker to reconsider his role in the battle between humans and the Nighlok.

episodes.name: Fight Fire With Fire
episodes.overview: The Nighlok Fiera unleashes an overwhelming attack on the Red Ranger, but when he goes down another Red Ranger takes his place. Which one is the real Red Ranger? The answer will change the Samurai Rangers forever.

episodes.name: The Great Duel
episodes.overview: As the Rangers attempt to adjust to being led by a new Red Ranger, Jayden struggles to find new meaning in his life.

episodes.name: Evil Reborn
episodes.overview: Jayden finishes his grand battle against Deker and the other Rangers try to convince him to rejoin their team before Master Xandred reawakens.

episodes.name: The Sealing Symbol
episodes.overview: With Master Xandred back on Earth, the Rangers finally attempt to use the Sealing Symbol to stop him - only to discover that he has a special new defense against it. Now, they must rise to the challenge and find a new way to defeat him and save the world.

episodes.name: Samurai Forever
episodes.overview: In a climactic battle, the Rangers face off against Master Xandred for the last time.

episodes.name: Stuck on Christmas
episodes.overview: The Samurai Rangers get stuck in the Megazord's cockpit on Christmas Eve when it breaks down after battling a Nighlok. Will they be able to make it out in time to celebrate Christmas?

19.name: Super Samurai
19.overview: The Samurai Power Rangers continue their battle against the evil Master Xandred who has now joined forces with the malevolent Serrator.  To fight this growing threat, the Samurai Rangers learn to use the legendary Black Box to form all new Megazord combinations and become Super Samurai.   Through teamwork, they also learn to invoke the power of their ancestors to morph into Shogun Mode and protect humanity from the Netherworld's vile villains.

episodes.name: Mega Mission
episodes.overview: When malicious aliens make their way to Earth's orbit, Gosei decides to form a new team of teenage heroes to defend the planet and carry on the proud tradition of the Power Rangers.

episodes.name: He Blasted Me With Science
episodes.overview: The alien invaders send Scaraba, an alien scientist, down to Earth to study the human race. Meanwhile, Troy finds himself face-to-face with Creepox.

episodes.name: Going Viral
episodes.overview: When Noah has trouble lifting Jake's heavy weapon, he begins to doubt his abilities, until he learns that believing in yourself is all that's necessary to get any job done.

episodes.name: Stranger Ranger
episodes.overview: As the Rangers learn that concentration is essential to perfecting their Ranger skills, they are distracted by a civilian falsely claiming to be a Ranger.

episodes.name: United We Stand
episodes.overview: Best Friends Gia and Emma are turned into bitter enemies by a vicious monster, Beezara. Meanwhile, the guys are captured by Beezara and turned into her slaves.

episodes.name: Harmony and Dizchord
episodes.overview: When Dizchord attacks the city with music that produces physical pain, the Rangers must fight back in an unorthodox way with a song of their own.

episodes.name: Who’s Crying Now?
episodes.overview: After Troy deals with some small-minded bullies at school, the Rangers square off against a more dangerous bully, Creepox.

episodes.name: Robo Knight
episodes.overview: The mysterious Robo Knight joins the Power Rangers. Can he help them defeat toxic monsters that threaten the Earth?

episodes.name: Prince Takes Knight
episodes.overview: While the Rangers are unsure about how to work with the newly-arrived Robo Knight, Vrak captures the robotic Ranger in an attempt to reprogram him for his own nefarious purposes.

episodes.name: Man and Machine
episodes.overview: When a shadow-stealing monster attacks, the Rangers must teach Robo Knight the power of teamwork in order to defeat him.

episodes.name: Ultra Power
episodes.overview: The Megaforce Rangers must find a powerful ancient weapon called the Wild Sword in the Black Mountains. Vrak plans to get to the sword first where he enlist the help of Distractor.

episodes.name: Last Laugh
episodes.overview: Gia, Emma, Troy, and Jake are captured by Nojoke during his capture of laughing people. Noah and Robo Knight must overcome their differences to free the captive Rangers and defeat Nojoke.

episodes.name: Dream Snatcher
episodes.overview: A dream-eating monster called Dream Snatcher preys on Emma after being enhanced by the Aurora Box that belonged to Vrak's family. The Rangers and Robo Knight must rescue Emma's dreams and defeat Dream Snatcher before the Roots of Despair emitted from his victims rot the Earth.

episodes.name: Gosei Ultimate
episodes.overview: Gosei and the Rangers must work together to defeat Bluefur and Bigs when they use the power of the Aurora Box.

episodes.name: Raising Spirits
episodes.overview: The Rangers have a strange encounter with a medium on Halloween.

episodes.name: The Human Factor
episodes.overview: The Megaforce Rangers encounter their first Robotic opponents, who try to convince Robo Knight that humans are the true danger to the Earth.

episodes.name: Rico the Robot
episodes.overview: When one of Metal Alice's robots malfunctions, Emma and the Power Rangers decide to adopt it and teach it the values of friendship and freedom.

episodes.name: Staying on Track
episodes.overview: The Megaforce Rangers must race to save the day when Metal Alice plots to throw the city into chaos by derailing a passenger train. Meanwhile, Robo Knight comes closer to understanding humans when he meets a young boy.

episodes.name: The Human Condition
episodes.overview: Admiral Malkor awakens from his cocoon stronger than ever and determined to destroy the Megaforce Rangers.

episodes.name: The Messenger
episodes.overview: The Megaforce Rangers' victory over the Warstar aliens is short-lived when they discover Metal Alice has turned Vrak into a powerful and menacing cyborg.

episodes.name: End Game
episodes.overview: When Cyborg Vrak, Metal Alice and The Messenger launch a vicious attack against the Megaforce Rangers, it will take all their powers and abilities to save the earth.

episodes.name: The Robo Knight Before Christmas
episodes.overview: Robo Knight learns the true meaning of Christmas from a group of children when he is mistaken for a donated Christmas toy and is shipped in a charity crate to a foreign land.

20.name: Megaforce
20.overview: For centuries, the earth has been protected by a supernatural guardian named Gosei and his robotic aide, Tensou.  When the evil Warstar aliens plan a massive invasion of Earth, Gosei calls upon five teenagers with talent and attitude to form the ultimate team…the Power Rangers Megaforce!  Using their newfound special abilities, mega-weapons, high-tech Zords and giant Megazords to battle this new alien threat, the Power Rangers Megaforce prove that “Earth's defenders never surrender!”  Go Go Megaforce!

episodes.name: Super Megaforce
episodes.overview: With that battle won, the civilians attempt to restore order. Back in the classroom, Mr. Burley lectures with new purpose, stating that when faced with great adversity the human spirit will always prevail. On the beach where Robo Knight fell, Troy remains pensive, more determined than ever to find their lost friend.

episodes.name: Earth Fights Back
episodes.overview: While the rest of the team works with the civilians to rebuild their city, Troy stumbles upon a plot by the Armada to launch missiles at major cities throughout the world.

episodes.name: Blue Saber Saga
episodes.overview: After being defeated in battle by a master swordsman monster called Skatana, Noah wonders if he is worthy to be a Power Ranger anymore and ends up training to counter Skatana's attacks.

episodes.name: A Lion's Alliance
episodes.overview: The Power Rangers take the Sky Ship to Animaria to look for the Red Lion Wild Zord. They soon find themselves in competition against General Peluso who is also after the Red Lion Wild Zord.

episodes.name: Samurai Surprise
episodes.overview: The emperor unleashes a powerful monster called Matacore to combat the Rangers. When fighting Matacore, the Power Rangers meet Jayden (the Red Samurai Ranger) and Mentor Ji who provide a disk to help them fight Matacore.

episodes.name: Spirit of the Tiger
episodes.overview: After the magnetic monster Pacha Chamak steals the Power Rangers' weapons, Jake and Emma consult with Casey Rhodes (the Jungle Fury Red Ranger who is now a part-time zookeeper) to learn a special form of martial arts.

episodes.name: Silver Lining (1)
episodes.overview: When the Armada sends down X Borg platoons after X Borg platoons, the Megaforce Rangers have their encounter with the Silver Ranger even when they are facing off against Gorgax.

episodes.name: Silver Lining (2)
episodes.overview: Orion explains his origins to the Rangers, Gosei, and Tensou. Meanwhile, Damaras sends Commander Osegain to Earth in a plot to destroy Orion.

episodes.name: Power of Six
episodes.overview: When the Rangers are sidelined by an energy-draining monster named Skeltox, Jake must get over his jealousy of Orion and help him master the powers of the Sixth Rangers in order to defeat Skeltox.

episodes.name: The Perfect Storm
episodes.overview: The Rangers are sidetracked from fighting Sirjinkor when Tensou develops amnesia and wanders away from the Command Center.

episodes.name: Love Is In the Air
episodes.overview: A love potion made by Invidious accidentally makes Levira fall in love with Jake. Upon discovering this, Invidious plans to eliminate Jake so that he can have Levira for himself.

episodes.name: United as One
episodes.overview: When the Legendary Megazord is damaged in a fight against Desolar (who is stealing the happiness from humans in order to cure Prince Vekar's cold), Emma uses unconventional methods to defeat this unusual monster.

episodes.name: The Grass is Always Greener... or Bluer
episodes.overview: A body-swapping monster named Tranceferer switches Jake and Noah's bodies while on a mission to swap the bodies of high-ranking people. While Tranceferer continues his mission, the monster Turtlelini is sent down to distract the Rangers causing Jake and Noah to handle fighting in each other's bodies.

episodes.name: In the Driver's Seat
episodes.overview: The Rangers are lured away from Earth and into Corinth by Professor Cog who locks the wormhole to Corinth. While the Rangers work to tame the Turbo Falcon Zord, Professor Cog and his Grinders attack Earth and runs into competition in the form of the Armada. The Rangers must find a way to tame the Turbo Falcon Zord and find a way back to Earth to stop Professor Cog.

episodes.name: All Hail Prince Vekar
episodes.overview: The Rangers finally battle Prince Vekar face to face when he comes to Earth armed with his very own Megazord.

episodes.name: Vrak is Back (1)
episodes.overview: Following Prince Vekar's destruction, Vrak resurfaces and makes his latest plan to destroy Earth with the help of a reprogrammed Robo Knight.

episodes.name: Vrak is Back (2)
episodes.overview: With two of the drills in the Earth, the Rangers must rescue Orion from Vrak and free Robo Knight from Vrak's control before the final drill can be placed.

episodes.name: Emperor Mavro
episodes.overview: Emperor Mavro comes to Earth following the deaths of his sons Vrak and Prince Vekar and replaces Prince Vekar's fleet with his own fleet. He also plans to punish Damaras for what happened to Prince Vekar, yet gives a chance to Damaras to redeem himself by destroying the Power Rangers.

episodes.name: The Wrath
episodes.overview: Emperor Mavro launches an attack on Earth by calling all Armada forces across the galaxy to drop what they are doing in their positions and head to Earth. He also sends Levira to fight the Rangers in order to redeem herself for the death of Prince Vekar and Vrak and to make up for Damaras' failure.

episodes.name: Legendary Battle
episodes.overview: When The Emperor nearly defeats the Rangers after a massive attack, the Rangers get help from Legendary Rangers from the past.

21.name: Super Megaforce
21.overview: Ruthless Prince Vekar has arrived with his massive alien Armada to conquer the earth.  To face this new threat, Gosei gives the MEGAFORCE RANGERS special Morphers and Keys, which allow them to morph into SUPER MEGAFORCE RANGERS!  Using these special Keys, they also have the amazing new ability to morph into any team of Legendary Rangers from the past.  Super-sized villains, super-sized powers and action-packed adventure can only mean one thing: the all-new POWER RANGERS SUPER MEGAFORCE has arrived!

episodes.name: Powers From the Past
episodes.overview: Millions of years after the mysterious and powerful Energems were entrusted to the now extinct dinosaurs for protection from a ruthless bounty hunter, a pair of courageous teens find themselves in possession of two of these long lost precious artifacts, and come face to face with a monster who will do everything in his power to steal them for himself.

episodes.name: Past, Present and Fusion
episodes.overview: A new teen finds his own Energem and joins Tyler and Shelby on their pilgrimage to the Dinosaur Museum, where they learn they are a part of the elite team called the Power Rangers. They are entrusted with protecting the Energems from a fierce bounty hunter named Sledge, who has returned and is more determined than ever to capture the Energems for himself.

episodes.name: A Fool's Hour
episodes.overview: Sledge arrives on Earth to confront Keeper and the Rangers. He gives them a deadline to return the Energems, but coming up with a plan to fight back gets compromised when Tyler goes after Fury on his own. Can the Rangers figure out how to work as a team?

episodes.name: Return of the Caveman
episodes.overview: Chase tries to help Koda adapt to modern day technology after he struggles to learn how to ride their new high tech Dino Cycles. But when they are caged in a cave by one of Sledge’s monsters, Koda must rely on his caveman instincts to escape and save his friend.

episodes.name: Breaking Black
episodes.overview: When a Maori fortune teller asks Chase for help guarding her shop from a potential thief, Chase is happy to help, but falls under a spell of Sledge’s latest monster, Spellbinder. The rest of the Rangers must quickly figure out how to help break Spellbinder’s hold on Chase before their friend is lost to them forever.

episodes.name: The Tooth Hurts
episodes.overview: When faced with the fast-firing Cavity monster, Riley thinks Chase doesn’t take the threat seriously, but soon learns that Chase simply has a different approach.

episodes.name: Let Sleeping Zords Lie
episodes.overview: When Sledge’s monster stings the Anklyo Zord, Shelby must use her advanced dino knowledge to tame the wild beast.

episodes.name: Double Ranger, Double Danger
episodes.overview: When clone Rangers steal the real Rangers' irreplaceable tracking device, Fury learns the location of the powerful Ptera Zord.

episodes.name: When Logic Fails
episodes.overview: The Maze monster, working with Fury, captures the Rangers until Riley's logical mind helps them break free. But the delay has allowed Fury time to head toward the Ptera Zord.

episodes.name: The Royal Rangers
episodes.overview: When the Rangers find the Gold Energem among the Royal Treasure, they decide to impersonate a Prince and Princess to lure Fury in and gain control of the power Ptera Zord.

episodes.name: Break Out
episodes.overview: Koda and the Rangers battle to save an arrogant prince and the Gold Energem.

episodes.name: Knight After Knights
episodes.overview: The Rangers must demonstrate their value to persuade their latest ally, the Gold Ranger, but find they do not have the willpower to do so when one of Sledge's monsters steals their courage.

episodes.name: Sync or Swim
episodes.overview: A fun rivalry between Tyler and Ivan becomes a problem when it interferes with the efforts of the Rangers to find and defuse a bomb planted by Sledge's monsters.

episodes.name: True Black
episodes.overview: When three Rangers become trapped in an underground tomb, it's a race against time for Chase to master his new power upgrade before his friends are lost forever.

episodes.name: The Ghostest With the Mostest
episodes.overview: When a monster kidnaps a Ranger and takes on their appearance during a Halloween party, Kendall must discover which of the team is the fake before their Energem is stolen.

episodes.name: Rise of a Ranger
episodes.overview: Prince Phillip discovers money can't buy the respect of an Energem when he embarks on his own quest to become a Power Ranger.

episodes.name: No Matter How You Slice It
episodes.overview: When one of Sledge's monsters manages to break the Rangers' bonds of friendship, it's up to Riley and Koda to remind their team what they truly mean to each other.

episodes.name: World Famous (In New Zealand)
episodes.overview: When one of Sledge's transport pods is spotted in New Zealand, the Rangers head to Auckland and are shocked to discover the existence of a new Ranger.

episodes.name: Deep Down Under
episodes.overview: With the Purple Energem in hand, the Rangers race to find the Plesio Zord before Sledge can destroy it for good.

episodes.name: Wishing for a Hero
episodes.overview: While searching for a new Purple Ranger, the teens find all their personal wishes coming true in the worst way.

episodes.name: Race to Rescue Christmas
episodes.overview: When Poisandra steals Santa's computer, it's up to the Rangers to get it back before Christmas is canceled.

episodes.name: One More Energem
episodes.overview: With two Energems in Sledge's possession, the Rangers and Kendall must take the fight to his ship in order to save the world.

22.name: Dino Charge
22.overview: Millions of years ago, an intergalactic bounty hunter named Sledge tried desperately to capture the 10 mysterious Energems, each capable of filling whomever possessed them with incredible powers. Keeper, the wise and ancient guardian of the Energems, entrusted each Energem to the Earth's mightiest beasts, the dinosaurs, for protection. Centuries later after the dinosaurs went extinct, some of the Energems were discovered by humans. Those who proved worthy gained the ability to morph into Power Rangers. But now, Sledge has returned and has vowed to capture the Energems at all costs. It is up to the Power Rangers Dino Charge to hunt down the rest of the Energems and defeat Sledge once and for all!

episodes.name: When Evil Stirs
episodes.overview: The Rangers believe their work is done after they've defeated Sledge and his evil monsters. Unbeknownst to them, an even more powerful monster is picking up where Sledge left off and is closer to the Rangers than they think.

episodes.name: Forgive and Forget
episodes.overview: Snide plans to contaminate the city water with venom that makes you forget who you are in hopes that the Rangers will be infected. Meanwhile, Riley has a score to settle with an old rival at the Amber Beach Marathon.

episodes.name: Nightmare in Amber Beach
episodes.overview: Shelby receives a pillow from an unknown sender. When she uses it to take a nap, she starts living a nightmare. The Rangers suspect this must be from Snide so they all make sure to stay awake, but that proves to be harder than they thought.

episodes.name: A Date with Danger
episodes.overview: Chase tries to impress his new girlfriend, Kaylee by showing how talented and accomplished he is. But when it becomes more about him and less about her, Kaylee starts to fall for the Black Ranger instead.

episodes.name: Roar of the Red Ranger
episodes.overview: Tyler tries to master the new T-Rex Super Charge Mode, but after Heckyl plants a virus in Kendall's computer, the T-Rex Super Charger malfunctions and makes Tyler go wild! Luckily, the Aqua Ranger is able to step in before it's too late.

episodes.name: Forged Under Fire
episodes.overview: Tyler looks forward to catching up with his dad after not seeing him for the past 10 years. When Tyler's Energem becomes cracked, he is forced to mend it by placing it in Hot Lava and prove to his dad he's not a kid anymore.

episodes.name: Home Run Koda
episodes.overview: Kendall creates a new Victory Charger that requires the core 5 Energems. But when Riley becomes Koda's coach on the Amber Beach Earthquake baseball team, he has a hard time pulling himself away from the game to help the other Rangers.

episodes.name: Riches and Rags
episodes.overview: When Ivan mistakes a thousand year old suit of armor as a training dummy, he finds himself in debt after destroying it. Heckyl sends in a hybrid monster named Spell Digger to spread greed to anyone who touches his gold coins.

episodes.name: Besties 4Eva
episodes.overview: Shelby's lifelong friend Erin starts to take credit for a song that Shelby wrote when they were kids. But when Erin starts to take credit for the work of the Pink Ranger, she quickly realizes how dangerous it can be to claim ownership of someone else's work.

episodes.name: Gone Fishin
episodes.overview: The Silver Ranger contacts Kendall from the far reaches of space to let them know where the location of a new Zord. When Singe and Fury intercept the message it becomes a race to see who can get there first.

episodes.name: Love At First Fight
episodes.overview: Poisandra's magic paint and brush are exactly what Beauticruel needs to make any guy she desires fall in love with her. Heckyl devises a plan to make the Rangers fall in love with her so he can steal their Energems

episodes.name: Catching Some Rays
episodes.overview: The Rangers discover the cave where Koda and his family once lived. Questioning the wise words of his Grandfather, Koda opens a section of the cave he was told to never enter, allowing an ancient monster to escape.

episodes.name: Recipe for Disaster
episodes.overview: Chase is determined to master a dessert recipe from New Zealand, when a food critic visits the Dino Bite Café. Meanwhile, an evil monster comes to earth to find the Energems and takes control of the Zords and Megazords.

episodes.name: Silver Secret
episodes.overview: Tyler joins Shelby in auditioning for an open spot on the popular New Zealand band, The N-Zed Boys. Meanwhile, an ally arrives, but not before the Rangers suspects he has an ulterior motive.

episodes.name: Trick or Trial
episodes.overview: The Rangers are forced to go to intergalactic trial for crimes against monsters.

episodes.name: Wings of Danger
episodes.overview: The Rangers learn the history of their Energems from a newfound ally. Meanwhile, an epic battle ensues in the forest over the Silver Energem.

episodes.name: Freaky Fightday
episodes.overview: A monster switches the Rangers' bodies, thereby creating trouble for them. Ivan meets his look-alike who turns out to be his great great great grandson.

episodes.name: Worgworld
episodes.overview: A new exhibit comes to the Amber Beach Museum: Worg, the robotic caveman. Arcanon sends a musician duo whose music can turn listeners into zombies.

episodes.name: The Rangers Rock!
episodes.overview: A new monster attacks the Rangers, turning most of them to stone. Shelby must work with Keeper to create a new Zord, the only plan that can save her friends.

episodes.name: Edge Of Extinction
episodes.overview: The Rangers find themselves needing help in their toughest fight yet as they do battle with Snide one final time, and Sledge's eggs hatch across the four corners of the Earth.

episodes.name: End Of Extinction
episodes.overview: The Dark Energem creates a black hole that takes the Rangers back in time, as they must go to a prehistoric age for their final showdown with Sledge and Fury.

episodes.name: Here Comes Heximas
episodes.overview: When the Power Rangers receive mysterious Secret Santa gifts, they uncover an evil plot to ruin Christmas.

23.name: Dino Super Charge
23.overview: The Power Rangers continue their search for the Energems after Sledge’s defeat, but soon learn that his most dangerous prisoner, the evil Heckyl, survived! In light of this new threat, Kendall creates a powerful new Dino Charger that unlocks the Red Ranger’s T-Rex Super Charge mode! It will take every Zord, Megazord, and Dino Charger in the Power Rangers’ arsenal to finally unite all ten Energems and save the universe!

episodes.name: Return of the Prism
episodes.overview: A young teen named Brody escapes to Earth from an alien spaceship with a special artifact called the Ninja Nexus Prism. He and two new friends must unlock its secrets to defend it from the villainous champion Galvanax.

episodes.name: Forged in Steel
episodes.overview: As Brody, Preston and Sarah return to Brody's childhood home in an attempt to find his lost family, Hayley and Calvin come across a strange alien named Mick.

episodes.name: Live and Learn
episodes.overview: Brody is accused of cheating on his first day of school after using his Data Comm to find answers. Now, he must use his own abilities and leadership skills to lead the Rangers against another threat from Galvanax.

episodes.name: Presto Change-O
episodes.overview: Preston is amazed to discover that he has developed real magical abilities; Galvanax hatches a plan with a new monster to steal the ninja power stars.

episodes.name: Drive to Survive
episodes.overview: When the Power Rangers are caught in the spider web prison of Galvanax's latest monster, Tangleweb, Calvin must conquer his fear to unlock a new power and save them.

episodes.name: My Friend Redbot
episodes.overview: Hayley is targeted by Galvanax’s latest monster. Isolated from the other Rangers, she and Redbot must work together to save themselves.

episodes.name: Hack Attack
episodes.overview: Determined to take part in as many student activities as she can, Sarah builds a device that allows her to clone herself, but the plan backfires when Galvanax's monster steals the technology for himself!

episodes.name: Gold Rush
episodes.overview: Both the Power Rangers and Galvanax attempt to find more information about the new mysterious Gold Ranger.

episodes.name: Rocking & Rolling
episodes.overview: Levi is excited to be embarking on his world tour, but as mysterious earthquakes start shaking up Summer Cove, he's presented with a tough decision.

episodes.name: The Ranger Ribbon
episodes.overview: When Summer Cove's sentimental "Ribbon Tree" is in danger of being cut down by Preston's wealthy father, Preston must learn to stand up to his father to save what is important.

episodes.name: Poisonous Plots
episodes.overview: Galvanax's latest contestant poisons Brody and the Rangers must make the ultimate sacrifice to save him.

episodes.name: Family Fusion
episodes.overview: The Rangers access a powerful new Megazord formation to battle Ripcon.

episodes.name: Ace and the Race
episodes.overview: Calvin finds himself increasingly distracted from his friends and Power Ranger duties when he spends all his time trying to impress his local hero.

episodes.name: The Royal Rival
episodes.overview: A mysterious princess and her royal guard arrive on Earth to challenge the Rangers.

episodes.name: The Royal Rumble
episodes.overview: The Power Rangers band together with a new ally to try and defeat Galvanax's new champion -- but even their teamwork may not be enough.

episodes.name: Grave Robber
episodes.overview: The Power Rangers celebrate Halloween by playing a spooky new board game, but find the stakes bigger than they imagined.

episodes.name: Monkey Business
episodes.overview: Hayley and Calvin's relationship is tested when they both decide to run for student body president.

episodes.name: The Adventures of Redbot
episodes.overview: Redbot documents the adventures of the Power Rangers on his new blog, while a cat-like monster attempts to steal the Ninja Power Stars.

episodes.name: Abrakadanger
episodes.overview: Preston must confront one of Galvanax's newest contestants after his magical spells backfire on his teammates.

episodes.name: Helping Hand
episodes.overview: While Sarah deals with issues at school, the Ninja Steel Rangers must overcome a force field.

episodes.name: Galvanax Rises
episodes.overview: Galvanax comes to Earth with a new, seemingly unstoppable plan to defeat the Power Rangers.

episodes.name: Past, Presents and Future
episodes.overview: Sarah teams up with Santa Claus to save Christmas and the Power Rangers from a time-manipulating monster.

24.name: Ninja Steel
24.overview: Deep in space, Galvanax is the reigning champion of the most popular game show in the universe, “Galaxy Warriors”. Galvanax sends his warrior contestants to Earth to steal the Ninja Power Stars, where each battle against the Power Rangers is broadcast throughout the universe. The Power Rangers must master their arsenal of Ninja Power Stars, Zords and Megazords to stop this evil threat and save Earth from destruction.

episodes.name: Echoes of Evil
episodes.overview: Madame Odius returns to Earth to track down the Ninja Nexus Prism.

episodes.name: Moment of Truth
episodes.overview: When Calvin forgets his and Hayley's anniversary, he panics and ends up a spinning a web of lies to cover up his mistake.

episodes.name: Tough Love
episodes.overview: Levi tries to change himself to impress a mysterious street performer.

episodes.name: Making Waves
episodes.overview: When a monster threatens Summer Cove, the Rangers tap into the power of a new Megazord.

episodes.name: Game Plan
episodes.overview: The students of Summer Cove High become addicted to a new video game.

episodes.name: Attack of the Galactic Ninjas
episodes.overview: The Galactic Ninjas arrive on Earth to destroy the Rangers once and for all.

episodes.name: The Need for Speed
episodes.overview: Sarah tries to break the world hoverboard speed record using a strange new technology.

episodes.name: Caught Red-Handed
episodes.overview: Brody is accused of stealing something from one of his teachers.

episodes.name: Outfoxed
episodes.overview: After their Zords are disabled by Odius' giant Foxatron, the Rangers must find a new way to stop her evil Zord.

episodes.name: Dimensions in Danger
episodes.overview: In a very special 25th Anniversary episode, the Super Ninja Steel Rangers team up with Legendary Rangers in an epic battle to save the world.

episodes.name: Love Stings
episodes.overview: Preston learns not to believe everything he hears.

episodes.name: Fan Frenzy
episodes.overview: Levi becomes overwhelmed by an overzealous fan.

episodes.name: Prepare to Fail
episodes.overview: Sarah and the team's overconfidence puts them all at risk.

episodes.name: Sheriff Skyfire
episodes.overview: A Space Sheriff is tricked into attacking the Rangers; Hayley learns an important lesson about respecting school rules.

episodes.name: Tech Support
episodes.overview: The Rangers need the help of an unlikely ally when their technology is infected with a computer virus.

episodes.name: Car Trouble
episodes.overview: Calvin is faced with a tough decision when he is offered his dream job.

episodes.name: Happy to Be Me
episodes.overview: When a monster steals Levi's voice, he learns an important lesson about self-worth.

episodes.name: Monster Mix-Up
episodes.overview: The Super Ninja Steel Rangers are ambushed by monsters who switch bodies with them.

episodes.name: Magic Misfire
episodes.overview: One of Preston's spells accidentally causes unintended consequences for one of his favorite teachers which he must now fix.

episodes.name: Doom Signal
episodes.overview: Odius has a devious plan to create a massive army to control the world.

episodes.name: Reaching the Nexus
episodes.overview: The Rangers must figure out how to save the citizens of Summer Cove and stop Odius once and for all.

episodes.name: The Poisy Show
episodes.overview: The Rangers look to celebrate Christmas but find their holiday cheer interrupted by an old foe.

25.name: Super Ninja Steel
25.overview: With Galvanax’s defeat and Brody and Aiden’s reunion with their father, all finally seems to be safe in Summer Cove. But when the Rangers are alerted to Madame Odius’ presence on Earth, they discover that she has obtained the powerful Ninja Super Steel and is still after the Ninja Nexus Prism! Luckily the Rangers are able to use the powerful new steel to create brand new Ninja Power Stars. It’s going to take everything in the arsenal, including brand new Megazords, to protect the Ninja Nexus Prism and defeat Odius once and for all!

episodes.name: Beasts Unleashed
episodes.overview: Scientists tap into the Morphin Grid, but an evil virus corrupts the technology and a new team of Power Rangers is formed to defend the Grid from evil.

episodes.name: Evox's Revenge
episodes.overview: When Grid Battleforce’s Commander needs to select a leader for the team, the Power Rangers are at odds over who should get the job.

episodes.name: End of the Road
episodes.overview: Zoey tries to convince the citizens of Coral Harbor to use Morph-X powered bikes instead of cars, but Blaze uses the opportunity to execute an evil plan.

episodes.name: Digital Deception
episodes.overview: Ravi is shocked when the evil Roxy comes to his rescue and wonders if there may still be good left in her.

episodes.name: Taking Care of Business
episodes.overview: Devon finds it difficult to balance a new job he took to impress his dad and the duties of being the Red Power Ranger.

episodes.name: Hangar Heist
episodes.overview: Nate develops new technology from a captured Gigadrone and Devon struggles with fully trusting his team.

episodes.name: A Friend Indeed
episodes.overview: Evox targets the Beast Bots to stop the Rangers from forming their Megazord.

episodes.name: The Cybergate Opens
episodes.overview: Scrozzle executes his plan to finally free Evox from the Cyber Dimension and the Rangers, along with an unexpected friend, must do everything in their power to stop him.

episodes.name: Silver Sacrifice
episodes.overview: The Rangers must band together to save one of their own from Evox's new plan.

episodes.name: Thrills and Drills
episodes.overview: Ravi must face one of his worst fears when it interferes with his Ranger duties.

episodes.name: Tools of the Betrayed
episodes.overview: An innocent lie leads to a break in trust between the Power Rangers.

episodes.name: Real Steel
episodes.overview: When Nate and Steel unexpectedly clash, it leads to double trouble for the team.

episodes.name: Tuba Triumph
episodes.overview: After witnessing a boy being bullied, Ravi takes him under his wing.

episodes.name: Hypnotic Halloween
episodes.overview: The Rangers are hypnotized into believing that they are the characters they dressed up as for Halloween.

episodes.name: Sound and Fury
episodes.overview: The Rangers' skills are put to the test when Blaze uses evil tech to massively enhance his Robotron's destructive power.

episodes.name: Seeing Red
episodes.overview: The Red Ranger gets amazing new powers, but they have unexpected side effects.

episodes.name: Gorilla Art
episodes.overview: Ravi resorts to drastic measures when Smash accidentally discovers a closely guarded secret.

episodes.name: Ranger Reveal
episodes.overview: When a movie star comes to town, the Rangers' secret identities are unexpectedly threatened.

episodes.name: Rewriting History
episodes.overview: The Rangers are brainwashed to think that Blaze and Roxy are part of their team.

episodes.name: Target: Tower
episodes.overview: Evox and his minions hatch the ultimate plan to take over the Morphin Grid.

episodes.name: Evox: Upgraded
episodes.overview: The Rangers mount a desperate mission to stop Evox once and for all.

episodes.name: Scrozzle's Revenge
episodes.overview: When the Rangers get trapped inside holiday ornaments, their Beast Bots must save both the Rangers and the city.

26.name: Beast Morphers (1)
26.overview: Set in the future, a secret agency combines a newly discovered substance called “Morph-X” with animal DNA to create the Power Rangers Beast Morphers team. The Rangers must fight off an evil sentient computer virus bent on taking over the source of all Ranger power, the Morphin Grid itself

episodes.name: Believe It or Not
episodes.overview: The Rangers are skeptical when Steel says he's found clues that proves Evox may have returned.

episodes.name: Save Our Shores
episodes.overview: A huge trash spill at the beach endangers the local wildlife; Scrozzle sets about finding reinforcements.

episodes.name: Game On!
episodes.overview: It’s not all fun and games when Devon’s favorite video game is brought to life in the form of a new Robotron.

episodes.name: Artist Anonymous
episodes.overview: Ravi secretly repaints a local art mural, but a strange artist arrives and claims the work as his own.

episodes.name: Cruisin' for a Bruisin'
episodes.overview: Devon discovers that Cruise has some skills that will help the Rangers in battle and pushes him to join the team.

episodes.name: The Blame Game
episodes.overview: Steel learns the concept of discipline and takes it too far, putting one of the Rangers in real danger.

episodes.name: Beast King Rampage
episodes.overview: The Rangers are given access to a powerful new Zord, but Evox has designs to steal it for himself.

episodes.name: Boxed In
episodes.overview: The Pan Global Games arrive in Coral Harbor, but Ranger duties prevent the teens from attending any of the events.

episodes.name: Secret Struggle
episodes.overview: Steel learns that Nate and Zoey have feelings for each other and tries to bring them together, despite the strict Grid Battleforce rules that forbid relationships between Rangers.

episodes.name: The Evox Snare
episodes.overview: Grid Battleforce shuts down the Morph-X towers to lure Evox into a trap.

episodes.name: Intruder Alert!
episodes.overview: The Rangers receive a strange message from outer space warning of an impending threat.

episodes.name: The Greater Good
episodes.overview: The Rangers do everything they can to help their new ally return home.

episodes.name: Finders Keepers
episodes.overview: A hasty decision by Zoey puts an old friend in danger.

episodes.name: Making Bad
episodes.overview: Evox decides to add a new villain to his team and commands his minions to find the evilest villain of all time.
